INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2518, 'Perth Royal Infirmary', '2001-02-27 00:00:00', '2001-02-28 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Joyce. Asked her to get everyone out of system and dialed on.  According to MB and WW They have been informed many times how to fix this problem, which involves clean system regularly as they do not have a lot of space. Core dump file in / was hugn. Removed file and space whent down to 57% used.  Told Joyce what to do in future. Checked backups and hasn\'t had a good all of Feb as users still logged in.  Told Joyce to check that the administrator should be cheking backups every morning. Call closed.Call reopened Scott Burden called, saying has informed us of this problem before.  He checks backup and does and whodb at 5pm to check users all logged out yet in morning backup shows processes still running. Is an ongoing problem.Scott will leave modem on so that we can dial in at 5pm to check if anyone logged in. Dialed in a 5pm. Two users still logged George Blaclk and Ronnie Sorieday. Spoke to George logging off now, unable to contact Ronnie Sorieday so left his session running as did not have authorisation to kill off.  Unable to contact Scott Burden. Sent Scott an e-mail informing him users still logged in and is there responsiblility to get good backups.KH 280201 - Dialed in to their system early and 9.15am.  Backup failed as expected due to user still logged in inhibiting shutdown. User \'rs\' has been logged in since 200201. Spoke to Scot Burden who has notified dept heads that user sren\'t logging out properly.  He will monitor the situation and make sure all users off system so get a good backup this evening. Suggested doing a manual backup today but not possible. Call closed.', 'Error message when try to kill print job \'Not enough pace on file system\'', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
