INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2521, 'Royal Hampshire County Hospital', '2001-02-28 00:00:00', '2001-02-28 00:00:00', 'Whilst doing a performance feedback an invalid employee code was entered and the record saved. Docket number 132741 employee code entered incorrectly is 752901. SQL delete record from hrs_wrkd uniquifier 6661. And edited cw_jon tot_hours_compl from 1.5 to 0.5 and lobour_costs from 16.05 to 5.35. Call closed.', 'System saved record with incorrect employee code.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2522, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2001-02-28 00:00:00', '2001-02-06 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Phil Lewis.All users are off. We have scheduled th cron backup to start at 14:00 today, while everyone is off. We will dial on tomorrow and check the log. REMEMBER TO RESCHEDULE THE CRON BACKUP FOR 20:00 IN THE EVENING.WW - Thu. 01/03/2001 - I have reset the cron to 20:00 hours.Their was a lot of corruption:add_inf, ph_j_det, ph_hist, as_dets, job_audt. These are rebuilt, and I will ask Phillip to do a manual backup when all is done. It looks like it will be finished today, so that the users can og on tomorrow. I will check the backlog tomorrow morning at 9:00am, and if everything is OK I will ask Phil to get his users to check out their work and make sure everything is still OK.WW - Fri. 02/03/2001 - Checked the backup and everything was OK. Got Phil to reboot the machine, after shutting down the databases. He is also looking into the weird Asset ID 8000 ph_hist records, that have no docket number. He will get back to me as soon as possible. I have also sent an email to Brian, at the request of Phil, about sending Phil a stern letter about backups and their importance. This is to help Phil impress upon his bosses the importance of backups, as they seem a little unconcerned?!WW - Mon. 05/03/2001 - I think that the weird asset_id 8000 records come from the financial control module in pharaoh. As an invioce comes in for a purchase order, and the purchase order is invoiced, then a record is written to the ph_hist table. It has no docket number etc.. I will ask Phil if this is correct.', 'Machine switched off when databases open and users logged on.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2523, 'Mid-Kent Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-02-28 00:00:00', '2001-03-01 00:00:00', 'call logged by Dave Thomas. Dialed in system had been turned off without shutting database first, so database had reopened as root instead of dbadmin.  Shutdb then pharaoh startdb. Unable to contact Dave by phone, sent e-mail informing him of how problem occurred, rminding him to shut databases before shutting system and that there may be corruptions. Told to check backup tomorrow morning and notify if any corruptions.WW 010301 - Call from Dave Thomas this morning. Backup log shows corrupted indexes for ph_hist. KH dialed on and rebuilt table. Ran volchk and piped through grep No errors. Removed no login and inform Dave Thomas to go back in but get good backup tonight. Call closed.', 'Error message when try to open database. -8913 couldn\'t open u2000.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2524, 'Royal Devon & Exeter Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-03-02 00:00:00', '2001-03-02 00:00:00', 'Kate logged in and ran:ps -A -o \"pid=\" -o \"pcpu=\" -o \"user=\" -o \"comm=\" | awk \'$2 > 5 {print $0}\' | sort -r +1which outputs all processes that consume more than 5% of the processing time. The culprit, consumming a continuous 98.98%, was a process called \'vhand\'. It appears to be started when the SCO is booted. I have asked Trevor to reboot, and see if that helps.Also the user \'vicky\' had a mail message, and it turns out that the system was sending her a message about being unable to print to the printer. System rebooted and everything running fine. Call closed.', 'Trevor is complaining of a system slowdown.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2525, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-03-02 00:00:00', '2001-03-07 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Helen Wesley.L and N type orders when invoices create record in ph_hist. Ph_full report will only total invoiced costs irrelevant of other un-invoiced order lines.KH 060301 - Spoke to Helen. She said report not showing orders that have been invoiced. Will fax through an example.WW - Wed. 07/03/2001 - The problem was that the report was expecting the ph_hist.ref_fld to be unique, but Helen had some duplicates from giving two or more invoices the same reference (which is fine). This meant that all the duplicate records where being lumped together as one record, and the first record was the only one where the values were showing. I have fixed this so that the report now receives the ph_hist.perm_history_id and does everything that it was doing for the ph_hist.ref_fld for the ph_hist.perm_history_id The fix will be released with Pharaoh 3.6', 'BUG2 - ph_full - Total sums up first order line only not sum of multile lines', 'Kate Hamilton', 1);
