INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (577, 'ALL SITES', '2000-03-23 00:00:00', '2000-05-23 00:00:00', 'Change to database setup:created with;creatdb -dpharaoh -vvol0 -Ovollen=8388608 -Ofiletype=regular -Opreallocate -Odesc=\'Pharaoh Database\'New dumpdd used including;4 x 100MB preallocated volumes (vol1, vol2, vol3, vol4) for data tables alone, stored in files (file1.db, file2.db, file3.db, file4.db)1 unlimited volume (volhash) for hash tables alone, stored in file (filehash.db)1 unlimited volume (volbtree) for btree tables alone, stored in file (filebtree.db)All the tables descriptions include the initial 4 volumes, and the data is scattered between them, no other tables will be used unless added. A new volume can be added to all tables with the dbaddvol command in $BINDIR.All the hash table descriptions include the hash volume (volhash), so that the hash tables only use that volume.All the btree table descriptions include the btree volume (volbtree), so that the hash tables only use that volume.Use a different version of dataserver (6.3BE).Waiting to here back from Unify about the problem.Heard back from Unify, They apparently have no log of my email, even though they asked me to send them the volchk output. I will resend them this and everything else they requested.WW - 08/05/2000Finnally got arround to trying John\'s suggestion, about rebuilding indexes once the data is loaded. This did not help much if at all. I also rebuilt all the history indexes as well just to see if that had any affect. Non. I emailed John with the news. I also resent him the access method output from the two databases, as he requested that I check that the access methods were the same for the two databases. Waiting for a reply. The reply was to use \'explain\' in interactive SQL to see the access methods used. Will work out what the SQL is that it is using, and then do the SQL.WW - Thurs 18/05/2000The problem lies in the \"order by\" clause. If this is removed from the form (F2 to get the info screen on the form) then the speed increases dramatically. RLT and PWD don\'t mind that the search results are not ordered by financial_year and period. They will pretty much be anyway as this is roughly the order that they will be entered in the database.I have made the changes to the form. I will PUT the form tommorrow, and compile. Then send the ph_hist, bit along with the correct unicap and termacp files to RLT for Tuesday 23rd when I create the JSB Beta test area.', 'System slowdown. Most noticable at - RLT, and PWD. Unify call number 16055', 'William Wragg', 0);
