INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (584, 'James Paget Hospital NHS Trust', '2000-03-20 00:00:00', '2001-03-09 00:00:00', 'KH LOOKING AT.After \'period end\' was run capital charges did not show the correct fiqures.  SQL used to fix by site.KH - Process Sarah used, tested  to replicate problem.  Interest calculated correctly, depreciation incorrectly?Logged as bug. Paper work in file.KH 010900 - Moved from BUG list to BUG2 list pending visit to James Paget by KH and JC as research.KH 151100 - Visit to James Paget with JC. This always happens on first period end run on assets commissioned from WIP.KH 130201 - If status flag is \'CW\' which means \'work in progress\' why have division/mu/cc/acc_code as WIP aswell? When commission asset from WIP will have to then assign a division/mu/cc/acc_code.  No charges are levied against cap asset when status is WIP.KH 140201 - Division: WE(WIP EQUIPMENT), WIP(WIP).  Management_unit: WE(WIP EQUIP) WIP(WIP).Cost_centre: WIP (work In Progress)   mu WIP   div WIP.KH 150201 - E-mail sent to Helen and Sarah asking 1.Why flag charge_type, price_index, group, division, management_unit and cost_centre as WIP when status_flag \'CW@ indicates Cap Asset as WIP and no charges levied.  2. Provided examples of cap assets that charges were incorrect after first period end after commissioned. If not amount difference.KH 270201 - After commissioning asset 20000 0027 then relocating it from WIP to CORS, then running period end no charges were levied against it nevermind the wrong charges.  Ran period again and still no charges. May have to revalue asset as well as relocate it after commissioning it. Still awaiting response of my e-mail dated 150201.KH 020301 - Spoke to Heken Harrison requesting reply to my e-mail. Request passed on to Sarah but very busy at moment, will respond as soon as possible.KH 050301 - E-mail from Sarah Smith giving their procedure on commissioning an asset. Unable to give example of incorrect charges on newly commissioned, problem is intermittent. Will give details as and when one arises cannot fix bug until have this inofmation. In meant time remianing life calculation incorrect, consequently replace date is incorrect.KH 060301 - Reply to Sarah\'s e-mail informing her unable to correct problem with more info/example and to provide one asap. In meantime will fix problem of replacement date. Replacement date is calculated by adding life span onto acceptance date which gives the remaining_life an extra period as replacement date is lifetime + 1.  Probable fix will be to calculate replacement date from acceptance date + life span - 1 day.KH 070301 - Modified ca_dets to subtract one day from acceptance date.  E-mail sent to Margery asking for clarification on the correct replacement_date and procedure if acceptance_date is after current period. E-mail reply from Margery.  Replacement_date is correct, it should be the date after the asset\'s life terminates.KH 080301 - E-mail sent to Sarah Smith and Helen Harrisson stating that replacement date is correct according to other Capital Charging user site.KH 090301 - Email from Sarah Smith saying replacemnet_date incorrect as they bring in asset as CI not CA so can charge strainght away. E-mail sent back saying will not alter code to cater for incorrect use of system. Call closed.', 'BUG2 - CC - Capital Charges period end incorrectly calculated on assets from Work in Progess to LIVE. And replacement date incorrect.', 'Kate Hamilton', 1);
