INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (586, 'Redbridge Healthcare NHS Trust', '2000-04-18 00:00:00', '2000-05-25 00:00:00', 'WW - 19/04/2000Changed SHMAX=8192k, left everything as before. Waiting to see what happens.WW - Fri 12/05/2000Have been trying to get hold of Lyn to ask her what is happening. Haven\'t been able to as of yet.WW - Fri 19/05/2000Got hold of Lyn. When she copied the live database to the training, and ran the year-end, the database ran out of space. Not disk space but volume space. This will mean increasing the size of the volumes. She wants a site visit Wednesday 24th. Will do a test dbdump (ascii) this evening at 5:30. Do not add the additional hashtables, as these might push the database over the edge. I added an additional volume, as an interim measure, until I can rebuild the database. They also had some problems with the live database not shutting down. Check their backup on Monday 22nd  to make sure that their was no corruption.WW - Mon 22/05/2000  No corruption. But they are still getting the LOGIN: ERROR see Task 2242Will do the test dump on Tuesday 23rd if possible. Speak to Lyn on Tuesday.WW - Tues 23/05/2000  Kicked off the dbdump. Stopped their crontab will need to start it again tommorrow if not going to them on Thursday.WW - Wed 24/05/2000  Will be going to Redbridge on Thursday 25th May: Get to Liverpool Street Station (Via Victoria) Go to Goodmayes Station (Not a Tube stop) Get a Taxi from just around the corner (tel 85990911) Drop at Main reception of Goodmayes Hospital. Ask for Lyn Wilson Ext. 2662WW 300500 - Year End finished with no problems. Database is now a multi-volume database.KH 050600 - Root & Boot disks sent back by courier.', 'Check their settings for Year End.', 'William Wragg', 0);
