INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (985, 'ALL SITES', '1999-02-02 00:00:00', '1999-02-02 00:00:00', 'ACPL -I$UNIFY/../include <formname>.fsHe states that this is causing the -I option to be passed to thec-preprocessor. This is correct.  Furthur, he says that in his experience, ACPL would not pass the -I option to the c-preprocessor on SCO.  This is in-correct.  ACPL will always pass the -I option on to the c-preprocessor, and all c-preprocessor\'s understand the -I option.  I believe that on AIX we configure the port to use someC preprocessor that is in some X windoes directory.  Sunil can let youknow where it is.  Whatever machine that you think does not pass the -I option to cpp is broken.  Can you let us know what machine/release has this problem. I am sure someone in porting can test this so we can determine a fix for it', 'ACPL not passing correct parameter list to cpp preprocessor in DS6 on SCO, AIX.', 'Adam Hardy', 0);
