INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (1446, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '1999-04-22 00:00:00', '1999-04-22 00:00:00', 'Figuring out exactly what Mike wants. Basically  the GRN date (grn_date in grn_dets table) is set as system date when the GRN is completed. Mike wants to be able to set this grn_date manually, to allow proper accruals to be made, i.e. He wants to be able to set the grn_date to the same date as the when the job/transaction etc. Was completed, as the GRN can be completed weeks later and so wont have the same date as the finished job/transaction. This he wants to achieve by putting a field in the \'order line\' section of the goods_rec (goods received) form - The \'Order line\' section can be got to via doing a next form (F2) on the goods_rec form - which will be a mandatory date field where any user can input the date they wish the grn_date to be.Additionally - Will have to talk to Mike again about the fact that completing a GRN also puts records into the ph_hist and sx_dets tables (depending on order type, \'L\' & \'N\' have a ph_hist record, while an \'S\' type order has an sx_dets record)  as well as the grn_dets table. Does he want the system date to be entered for these, or does he want the date to be the new manually entered date?', 'PO: GRN - currently defaults to system date for GRN entry, doesn\'t allow date change. Need ability to change date to allow proper accruals / resource accounting - Enhancement request', 'William Wragg', 0);
