INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2165, 'James Paget Hospital NHS Trust', '2000-03-20 00:00:00', '2001-02-14 00:00:00', 'KH Looking at..by the apportionments from (ap_dets) when relocating or commissioning an asset.(outstanding call with Ali).KH 010900 - Moved from BUG list to BUG2 list pending visit to James Paget by KH and JC as research.KH 151100 - Visit to James Paget with JC.  Apportionments not updating ap_dets therefore charges for asset go to wrong/old cost centre.KH 220101 - Upon confirming bug think table that is not being updated is ca_dets not ap_dets.  Apportionment amendments can be done in ap_dets form.  Changed DIV/COST CENTRE and ACC CODE and ap_dets has `updated but ca_dets has not.  After taking down details regarding each charge code and changed to cap_add_id (1006 and 11662) to a different charge code and a 50% split between 2 charge codes, respectively I ran charges run.  Appears to be using the most recent charge code. So for whole change was fine but for split only took 50%.  Need to speak to Helen to check what she has noticed. Should be security to disallow deletion of line in ap_dets relating to details in ca_dets.KH 230101 - According to spec changes to div/man unit/cost centre/acc code shoud be done in \'Amend Capital Asset Details\', \'Relocate Asset\'. Then Apportion it to other s if necessary. Will check code for reloc.fs  to see if/how updates ap_dets.KH 310100 - reloc.fs mentioned new account_code, cost_centre, division and management_unit but does not display update for ca_dets. Amend.fs also does not display update to ca_dets or reference account_code, cost_centre, division and management_unit. Reason.fs does show ca_dets update so will add update to ap_dets here.KH 010201 - Modified reason.fs, added update SQL to update ap_dets with new account_code, cost_centre, division, management_unit where donated flag is set to N. Specified in reloc form. Tested and doe