INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2166, 'James Paget Hospital NHS Trust', '2000-03-20 00:00:00', '2000-12-19 00:00:00', 'Priority 23 : Time 2 days..if adding, commissioning or revaluing assets. SQL currently being used to fix.(outstanding call with Ali).KH 210700 - Added 2 new capital assets, replacement date calculated correctly. Tried to revalue new assets 1231233 and 1231234 program did not display any error but revaluation does not show in ca_dets.KH 240700 - Entered new asset with status CW, then commissioned it, replcaement date calculated correctly.  Tried to revalue an asset worked correctly.  The remaining life however always seems to be incorrect.KH 260700 - Email sent to Sarah Smith asking for info on how replacement date and remaining life should link/be calculated.KH 270700 - Apparently Sarah Smith on leave this week hope to received response to email on Monday 31st July.KH 090800 - Email from Sarah quoting SQLs she uses to change replacement date and remaining life, not what I asked for, so still don\'t know how she gets the correct date to SQL in.  Fax received from Sarah, 14 pages of cc procedures.KH 100800 - Email sent to Sarah asking for formula for calculating correct remaining life.KH 010900 - Moved from BUG list to BUG2 list pending visit to James Paget by KH and JC as research.KH 151100 - Visit to James Paget with JC.  When commisioning an asset. When revaluing asset only buildings. DV revalues entire estate every 5 years.  When they create.revalue asset they always make  the acceptance date the 1st of the curernt month as a CI so that depreciation starts right away from that time.  According to Jos The program automatically assumes then effective date for depreciation as the 1st of the next month.  Helen/Sarah said they keep getting 1 extra period for remaining life and the replacement date is the 1st of April not 31st March. JC said this is because the program starts from