INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2213, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2000-05-18 00:00:00', '2000-05-19 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Margery Griffin. ca_dets showing remaining life as 12 when should be 8. Investigation showed no charges_update for previous year therefore included in remaining life calculation. SQL\'d dummy charge date in and asked Diane to enter another capital asset. Diane said system now automatically calculates replacement date and cannot enter correct date sooo did not add asset soooooo does not know if remaining life calculating correctly.WW - Fri 19/05/2000Looking into the access to replacement date field in ca_dets screen. You can access it for ANY Depreciation type, not just variable life, when there are no charges runs listed in fin_pers.  But you cannot when there are. The program is supposed to break out when there are no charges runs, and NOT ALLOW THE RECORD TO BE SAVED, but doesn\'t - I supppose it should really execute the \'next action is clear to find\' command, as this will end execution of the \'clear to add\' section and then start the \'clear to find\' section, so blanking clearing all the filled in data from the screen. The only time you can change the replacement date is through the \'Amend assets\' screen for assets with a depreciation type of \'D\'.', 'Capital Charging displaying incorrect remaining life and DBERRO status 118 inserting in ch_hist', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2214, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2000-05-18 00:00:00', '2000-06-21 00:00:00', 'Sonia will send me an email with the report, and the further info.WW - Fri 19/05/2000 Received Sonia\'s e-mail We spoke regarding  looking into the coding of \'delivery date\' taken from the order line against Original orders using the latest delivery date where there are V.O\'s. If it is posiible we would like you to do the work .Confirmation of this will be forthcoming from Mike if feasible.  The report we are using at present can be found as follows:sql_work, mikemc.sh, custom, menu_user, menu_userreports hope this helps SoniaWW - Mon 22/05/2000  Looking into time feasability and time. Look at doing the report first, and then at pharaoh coding. Downloaded the requisite shell script, queries and report.  It will take 2-3 days probably. Could update the shell script, or add another accell report to the second menu of their pwdrpts program. Spoke to Sonia, she will speak to Mike, who will probably say go ahead. They would like it before the end of June AT THE LATEST. Aim for mid June.WW - 20/06/2000Completed, and installed.', 'BESPOKE WORK - Additions to a report, or pharaoh code, so that they can report on overdue orders, and to take account of variation orders which extend the orders due date.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2215, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2000-04-17 00:00:00', '2000-07-21 00:00:00', 'Jos wrote: The NHS Supplies provide a servoce to all the Trusts in Tayside and Angus and will not consider using PHARAOH.Ninewells would prefer to use a method of data transfer to get the information from the NHS system into PHARAOH, ie, by downloading into a spreadsheet and import, or to a disc or EDI. The imported data would need to update the ph_spare table with the following:-*docket_no, stock_no, stock_desc_1, quantity_used, and cost. It may also have to hold a default locat_code.The date issued may not be required as the date of docket feedback would be close enough.WW - Wed 19/05/2000 They need to record the materials costs against an asset.                              Already attributed to job. Need to get                              Pharaoh to do the same issuing, or+--------------------+      record it in ph_hist as if it was issued          +--------------------------------------+ | NHS Stores | ------------------------------------------------------------------------>| Pharao cw_job/ph_hist |+--------------------+      against a closed job.                                   +--------------------------------------+I estimate that this will take 6-7 days to do including spec. Told Jos this, he seems happy.WW - Fri 21/07/2000 - Due to some finacial difficulties of theirs they will not be wanting the Mod any time soon.', 'BESPOKE WORK - There is a requirement at Ninewells hospital to record against dockets the stock issues that are made from the NHS Supplies stores. The NHS Supplies have their own software package which covers Purchase Orders and Stock Control.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2216, 'Eastbourne General District Hospital', '2000-05-12 00:00:00', '2000-09-05 00:00:00', 'BESPOKE WORK - NHS Supplies Mods - WWCompleted just needs to be installed.[nhs_sup.fs], [nhs_sup.fq], [nhs_sup.rs], [nhs_sup.rp] : CREATED, COMPILED, TESTED, PUT, .CHANGES UPDATED[amend_ord.fs] : GOT, AMENDED, TESTED, TESTED, PUT, .CHANGES UPDATED[com.fs] : GOT, AMENDED, TESTED, TESTED, PUT, .CHANGES UPDATEDScheduled for 4th Sept. at 4:30pm, give John a ring at around 4:00pmEastbourne want to use the full facilities of the Financial Control module for Purchase Orders but they are contrained by the fact that they have to use the NHS Supplies system.Jos wrote: This would at the moment entail raising a purchase request in PHARAOH, ie. Raise a Purchase Order and print if off to get an order number, and forwarding this to the Supplies department who then raise a Purchase Order in their system.A suggestion I put forward to them was to use the oh_dets, order_desc field to enter the Supplies order number in. This is a 40 character field which is not printed on the order. It would mean adding a \"stop for input\" statement into the Amend Issued Ordders\" program so that they could enter the NHS Supplies Order number. This is a search field and would act as the cross reference field.Jos needs an estimate of the time this will take to implement.WW - 22/06/2000John is back on the Mon 26th June, Will speak to him then about the work. As it appears that we will have to manually enter the purchase order value, rather than letting it auto create and using the order_desc field , as all the reports are geared towards the order_number field, so you could not do reports on the NHS Spares order number.WW - Tues 04/07/2000John was not in his office, and will not be back in until Fri 07/07/2000WW -Thurs 03/07/2000Spoke today, discussed the work. We will go with Jos\'s original idea of using the oh_dets.order_desc field. This will only require a change to the \'Amend Issued Orders\' screen so that the oh_dets.order_desc field is accessable and ammendable, This will be switched on and off by a $CUSTOM/pharaoh file variable. They will also require a new form/report that cross references the pharaoh order numbers (oh_dets.order_number) and the NHS Supplies order numbers (oh_dets.order_desc).WW - Tues 05/09/2000Emailed the parts, as could not download them because of their fire wall. Waiting to find out when they have been put onto the server. DONE', 'BESPOKE WORK - NHS Supplies Mods - WW', 'William Wragg', 0);
