INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2228, 'Redbridge Healthcare NHS Trust', '2000-06-06 00:00:00', '2000-06-13 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Lyn Wilson.  When Will was on site 25May2000 he put stars in all the blank fields.  Now when doing docket feedback system recognised SOMETHING in the mandatory fields and allows the docket to be completed, however when try to archive it system does not recognise the data in the mandatory fields. Example 176075.  Spoke to Will, Stars correctly represent nulls, thus system should not accepting the feedbacks.  I will ask Lyn what error message comes up when trys to transfer to history/archive, and if still happening on new jobs.KH 070600 - Lyn says new jobs have stars in the blanks field. Error message when transferring to history is \"Failed to transfer due to missing budgets\".  Will continue to check of jobs until remedy found.  PPM Job List and stock reports not identifying information that should be.KH 080600 - After much research DBDUMP and DBLOAD are buggered and TDUMP and TLOAD are fine. Jos and I ran a tload on a table when had filled with stars doing a dbdump/dbload, dumpfile had removed stars, ran tload and stars are gone. SORTED! Intend running tdump/tload at across modem tomorrow morning.KH 090600 - Dialed into their system, checked backup, problem with data.train but will over write it with live. Disabled the database.  Tdump activated. Tdump completed in 3hrs10. No data.blank so unsure how to remove data from tables, waiting for Will to contact us. tdel is the program to delete data from tables. Copy of their database done. Tdel started 16:30. Tdel still running at 21:30.  KH 100600 - session hung, unable to check progress. Redbridge IT call out not prepared to reset modem.KH 120600 - Dialed in tdel finished 5am sat. 13 hrs processing!!  No backup Friday due to tdel running.  Tload set off at 9.30am. Still running at 5pm, Crontab rescheduled to run at 1am.KH 130600 - dialed in tload finished 18:18. Backup complete although some tables were overloaded.  No stars appearing on screen. CASE CLOSED.', 'Archiving unsuccessful as completed dockets have mandatory fields full of stars (*).  Turns out Starts are across the whole database where a fiels is null.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
