INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2259, 'ALL SITES', '2000-07-26 00:00:00', '2001-02-09 00:00:00', 'WW - LOOKED INTO. [stk_rtiss.fs] SEE BELOW FOR MORE DETAILS.[stk_rtiss.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated.Raised fault report. Issued all 8 of stock code 4730002 to docket no 88. Total value of stock was 36.19 - unit proce 4.52.  Total value of 36.19 charges to job when docket feedback completed.  Having completed job and checked stock levels history, stock transactions and financial transactions, returned 4 items of stock code 4730002.  Program returned 4 items to the stock location at the unit proce the were issued ie 4.52, total value 18.08.  Checked stock levels, showed 4 at 4.52, total value 18.08. Checked stock transactions and 4 were entered at 18.08. Checked financial transactions - adjustment OK.  Check stock transactions - adjustment OK.  Check permanent history - adjustment to materials cost was not adjusted. Still showing 102.19, should be 84.11.WW - Mon. 05/02/2001 - The spec and the code explicitly avoids updateing the materials costs in permament hiostory, even though current works jobs have their materials costs updated?! Spoke to Jos about this, he still maintains that they should be updated in permanent history, just like they are in current work. This will not be too difficult, as just need to copy the current work section in stk_rtiss.fs and modify it for permanent history.', 'BUG2 - AO - ph_hist - Permanent History  file not displaying recalculted materials cost after adjustment', 'Jos Cooper', 1);
