INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2315, 'ALL SITES', '2000-09-21 00:00:00', '2003-02-11 00:00:00', 'Kate Installed onto startrek, but cannot creatdb, get the following errors:creatdb: Unable to create data base;    Unable to access configuration source file (i.e. \'file.cf\')    typically due to inadequate operating system resources or permissions. (-1376)<When a file.cf is added get the following errors>creatdb: Unable to create data base;    The database physical log file (i.e. \'file.pl\') cannot be accessed.pharaoh> fmdmn: Unable to activate database \'/u1/pharaoh/pharaoh_ds6/data.quick/file.db\';    The database physical log file (i.e. \'file.pl\') cannot be accessed.<This creates these records; errlog   file.cfg   file.db    file.err ><When file.pl added get the following errors;>creatdb: Unable to create data base;    Could not create shared memory - incorrect SHMKEY value? (-61)Pharaoh> fmdmn: Unable to activate database \'/u1/pharaoh/pharaoh_ds6/data.quick/file.db\';    Could not create shared memory - incorrect SHMKEY value? (-61)Phoned Unify not much help. Should just be able to type \'creatdb\' to create a blank db. Will phone again Fri 22nd.WW Fri 22nd Sept. 2000 - Reinstalled DS6.3BE and relicensed, still no luck. Phoning William at Unify. WW Thur 28th Sept. 2000 - Phoning and emailing William at Unify. Still no luck.KH 031000 - Support person (William) to call me back. Willam phone said Still investigating problem, as cant find reason.  Will speak to other sites to see if problem exists there and will speak to UNIFY USA for advice. Will phone back this afternoon.KH 041000 - William at UNIFY suggested check settings and different license key. No change.KH 051000 - Successfully installed and ran ds6.3AB on scoweb. Ds6.3BE installed onto scoweb but again failed to run creatdb - creatdb: Unable to create data base; Unable to access configuration source file (i.e. \'file.cf\')  typically due to inadequate operating system resources or permissions. (-1376).  Spoke to William and sales person Carol Hanson, another copy will be sent out.KH 111000 - New Copy of ds6.3BE on CDROM received by DHL. Installed on scoweb, but creatdb still failed.  Unable to create database.  Unable to access configuration source file (ie \'file.cf\') typically due to inadequate operating system resources or permissions (-1376).  Spoke to William who asked us to check README file and to install from scratch inc environmentals. WW spoke to William, USA site will install 3BE and try to replicate problem.KH 081100 - Email from William Erinle to WWW forwarded to me with further changes to env settings before running cretdb. Error message still appears. WW speaking to William re further action.WW - Thurs. 9th Nov. 2000 - I sent a message to the unify list and got some responses. The solution turned out to be as outlined below;Thanks to those who replied.  It turns out (thanks Odemir) it had to do withthe way that ds6.3BE handles memory segements compared with ds6.3AB. It wasnot the MAXCACHE that was the problem, as this was set as \'undefined\'. Theproblem seems to be with the unify SHMMAX. The default for unify SHMMAX is512k and for unify SHMMIN is 128k. Now as Odemir said, if ds6.3AB could notget the full amount of shared memory then it would try and get the biggestvalue above the unify SHMMIN value. Ds6.3BE seems to want the exact and fullamount?! When I changed the system value of SHMMAX to 12MB everything wasfine.I only have manuals for ds6.3AB and it says that the default for unifySHMMIN is 128k, if the default has changed in ds6.3BE to the same as SHMMAX,I would expect to get exactly the same memory sharing problems. The onlyslight problem with the obove theory is that the original setting for thesystem SHMMAX was 512k, which is why I never thought to check the sharedmemory settings. I have just run \'creatdb\' again to check on the size of theshared memory segment that was created, and it turns out to be 512k? Butadditionally it has created the cache memory segment as well? It did not dothis before, so Odemir was right, and it is the MAXCACHE setting andds6.3BE\'s desire for the exact amount. As MAXCACHE defaults to 1000, 512ksystem SHMMAX would be approx. 4 times too small.KH 110203 - WW says close as no longer an option. Task closed.', 'DEVELOPMENT - ON HOLD - Trialling of DS6.3BE - Unify Log number: cts18103', 'William Wragg', 0);
