INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2344, 'Perth Royal Infirmary', '2000-10-30 00:00:00', '2000-12-04 00:00:00', 'Raised by James. He spoke to Mike who sent it to me. I tried to get hold of James in the afternoon to get more info, e.g. what on earth is a diverted time card docket? But I could not get through to him. Jos does not know what a diverted time card docket is either.WW - Wednesday 1st Nov. 2000 - changed /etc/lp1 to a simple cat ( cat $1 > /dev/tty7 ) as it was set up for the vision spooler. We are hoping that that was the problem, as when I changed their default printer spooler (in the asset operational control file) from \'lp -s\' to \'printcon\' (as everyone else has) and set the PRINT_METHOD to \"file_print\", the output file was fine and did not stop before finishing the docket. James will phone me tomorrow to tell me how it went.WW - Wed. 151100 - Still waiting to hear if everything is sorted or not. Phoned end of last week, and James said that he would be testing it.WW - Thurs. 231100 - Spoke to Scott, he will try and add a new print server to replace the shiva print server on the problem printer. He is dealing with the problem. Will reopen if they phine again.', 'Docket Printing - The page does not advance to next page when the docket is a \'Diverted Time Card\' ?', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2345, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2000-10-30 00:00:00', '2000-10-30 00:00:00', 'changed the length in the unix queue to 66, after checking that their were no headers or margins set. Will get Gordon to try again, and if that doesn\'t work will get him to swap the printer for a laser jet 6 or something.I changed the print length in pharaoh to 64, as this is what it was in printer spooler. I also amended the report so that it didn\'t skip two lines at the start of each docket. And everything works fine.', 'Docket printing on Gordons Deskjet 4 - hpl4 (unix queue). The prints are starting 2 lines too far down the page, so each new print creeps further and further down the page as the prints come out.', 'William Wragg', 0);
