INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2348, 'Royal Hampshire County Hospital', '2000-11-01 00:00:00', '2001-02-08 00:00:00', 'WW - LOOKED INTO. FOR FURTHER DETAILS SEE BELOW.[tr_to_hist.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[pa_fb1.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.Can\'t find any reason for the error in the code. Told Bill Watkins to carry on pressing return until the message goes away, he only had to press return a few more times until the transfer carried on. Will carry on looking into this problem.After further investigation it appears that it has something to do with the blank docket numbers. The code in this area seems riddled with possible errors. The code does not use the uniquifier to delete or copy hrs_wrkd or cc_phist. Will change this code - after figuring out what causes the error - in the next version of pharaoh (3.6).WW - Tue. 06/02/2001 - After Further investigation it appears that if there are multiple hrs_wrkd records with no docket number, all the same except for the uniquifier column, then when one of them gets transferred to history (cc_phist) and gets deleted from the hrs_wrkd table, it deletes all the other records with the same details. Therefore when the next record in the set of records with the same details gets transferred to history, it cannot delete itself from the hrs_wrkd table, as the previous record has already done this. The solution, is to either ignore the status -35 error, and right code to ignore it, or use the uniquifier column, to do the selection and deletion.', 'BUG2 - CW - tr_to_hist - db error deleting hrs_wrkd status -35 when trying to transfer to history (tr_to_hist).', 'William Wragg', 1);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2349, 'Royal Hampshire County Hospital', '2000-11-01 00:00:00', '2000-11-16 00:00:00', 'Will try to dial on to his system to look at them sometime this, or next week.KH 081100 - attempted to dial in but no one available to turn on modem.KH 141100 - Dialed in via Roger. Bill Watkins provided docket number relating to problem:36527.  File does not exist in cw_job, does exist in ph_hist yet comes up in performance feedback.   The following tables are effected in xfer program INSERT: ph_hist, ph_j_dets, ph_w_don, ph_spare, cc_phist, fx_dets, cost_hist.  DELETE: cw_dets, wk_done, spares, hrs_wrkd, jb_costs, cw_job.  SQL shows all tables in DELETE for above docket.pm_ID have been deleted except for hrs_wrkd.  In INSERT some tables are empty but I think they not mandatory tables. Will continue Thurs 16 Nov as on site 151100.KH/WW 161100 - deleted row from hrs_wrkd relating docket 36527, after confirming all other information was where it should be. Call closed.', 'Will Watkins reported that he has a couple of jobs from 1997 that he cannot delete. They appear in feedback, but say that they are already closed, but don\'t appear in current work?', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2350, 'North Derby CHCS', '2000-11-02 00:00:00', '2003-06-23 00:00:00', '[$BINDIR/rptcon]: ammended, tested[com.fs]: got, changed, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[print_rep.fs/fq]: created, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[ptr_zm.fs]: got, changed, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[ids_defaults.h]: got, changed, tested, put, .changes ammended[jd_print.fs/fq]: got, changed, tested, put, .changes ammended[$PHABASE/lib/schema.380]: ammended, testedHe has a normal dot matrix printer that prints onto pre printed dockets, this is printer that the current job_docket report is printed out too. He is going to install a laserjet on a remote site, and wants an A4 job docket report for this printer. Tower Hamlets has a system installed for using different reports for different printers. I will dial in and look at what they do.The Tower Hamlet system is one that everybody has, but it does not change a report script, but just runs a script on the report script to change it on the fly. The order of events that goes to make a print prevents the \'rptcon\' script knowing what printer it\'s print is going too, and the \'printcon\' script from knowing or changing the report:(1) ASCII text from SQL(2) rptcon <report script name> <printer | screen | file> [page_length](3) printcon <print_queue>(1) is piped to (2) and (2) is piped to (3).If the <printer | screen | file> section of \'rptcon\' could also have the printer queue passed to it then \'rptcon\' would then know that it should output to a printer, and what printer that was. E.g.rptcon <report script name> <printer | screen | file | printer_queue> [page_length]rptcon /u/pharaoh/aclenc/com/ao_cw/reports/jd_print.rp -dlp1 66The printer queue is the printer name postfixed with \'-d\' as is the standard in pharaoh.This would allow rptcon to know which printer it was printing to. It would not be able to change the printer, but it would be able to switch the report which it was using, depending on the printer.If I was to do this the jd_print form and any others that this was required with would need to be changed and recompiled. I would have to change the \'rptcon\' script as well. If I left the \'printer\' switch in it would still work fine with all the other forms.', 'DEVELOPMENT - [WILL] - 3.8 - Bob errat wants different job dockets run depending on which printer the job dockets are printed out on.', 'William Wragg', 0);
