INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2379, 'East Kent NHS and Social Care Partnership Trust', '2000-10-23 00:00:00', '2000-12-19 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Dave Mastin via letter dataed 12/10/00.  Spoke to JC and told him that may be similar case of using series incorrectly.  JC looking into.WW - Fri. 01/12/2000 - From investigations with the JSB database the following has been deduced:(1) The problem is only with the \'PM year planner\' form (pmyear) and does not affect the actual transfer of jobs. The jobs get transferred correctly, despite what the pmyear planner says.(2) The problem only happens if the user is in \'standard weeks mode\', if the user is in \'low weeks mode\' then the problem of jobs falling out of sync and moving on a week each year, does not occur.WW - Mon. 04/12/2000 - Spoke to Dave about the above, and said that in the current year it seems to predict the behaviour of the jobs OK, it\'s only when you do future years that they get out of sync. He will have a go at printing them out in January, and see if this is true. Meenwhile I will try and fix the Year planner program to accurately pridict future years, ie. Find out where it\'s adding the extra week.WW - Wed. 06/12/2000 - [pmyear.fs] - got, amended, <tested, put, .changes updated>Currently testing the changes.WW - Mon. 12/12/2000 - [pmyear.fs] - got, amended, <tested, put, .changes updated>Made some more chnages, as the testing and Tevor Man\'s output indicated that their were more problems with the year planner code. Now re-testing. WW - Tues. 12/12/2000 - Problems fixed. Will send him the fix when made the changes to RDE\'s problems with the same form. See task 2438WW - Tues. 19/12/2000 - [pmyear.fs] - got, amended, tested, put, .changes updated', 'BUG2 - AO - pmyear - pm_job for same asset but different frequncy falling out of sync.', 'Kate Hamilton', 1);
