INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2383, 'Royal Dundee Liff Hospital', '2000-10-25 00:00:00', '2000-11-15 00:00:00', 'call logged by Eric Olgilvie. Probably because all work is now carried out on their server, making the whole process a lot slower than vision. Told Jos this.KH 091100 - Still taking a very long tim to search in pm_job. Some time minute and a half on F3. Call reopened 091100.  Eric stated \'Nothing\' has changed in their user situation.  WW thinks maybe updated search criteria in pm_job as part of enhancements asked for by users, invloving extracting data from another table and appending to pm_job for asset site, management_unit etc.  WW recreating system environment here to see if same search time occurs.  Dundee liff do have a slow machine resulting in slow searches with this new function.  Other site have more efficient machines and thus haven\'t had a problem with it. WW produced Patch091100 which will reduce the speed of the search in pm_job and hopefully reduce the time for project searches aswell.  Managed to load patch091100. Patch101100 unsuccessful, sz failed to pick up file although went through the motions.KH 131100 - sz decidee to work this morning. Eric will have Glenys get all users out of Pharaoh at 12.30 today. Glenys logged call regarding the creation of po.  If F2 into order line description get error message and stuck.  Investigation shows wrong 091100patch done. Was for SCO not AIX. Re did patch091100 for AIX and did patch 101100 which helps to reduce search time on pm_job. Call closed.WW -151100 - call reopened. 151100patch created to fix the projects slowdown. Will phone them today and see if I can dial in and install it today.', 'When searching in pm_job and pj_code_dets is very slow.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
