INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2395, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2000-11-16 00:00:00', '2003-02-10 00:00:00', 'WW - Mon. 05/02/2001 - Spoke to Rob Grub in the Estates Supplies department, and he will be getting back to me, probably via email, beginning of next week, with the format and examples of the information that they will be suppling them.WW - Mon. 19/02/2001 - I have written the spec and emailed it to Gordon. I am expecting both him and Rob grub to sign the email and send it back. Awaiting call from Gordon. The rough outline is that and awk script will be run from within the nhs_sc_iss form (this is a new one created in the stock transactions menu) in the before form section, and will load any outstanding data from the nhs supplies people into a new table, nhs_sup. The form will then interegate the new table, and transfer any required stock to the current work file. The stock used will be created as dummy stock items in the stock system. The amounts of stock will not be kept tabs of in the stock system, only the different stock items used. All the nhs supplies transfers will be kept in the nhs_sup table and flagged as transferred when they have been.WW - Wed. 28/02/2001 - Still not heard from them or had any confirmation for a go ahead.WW - Wed. 07/03/2001 - Still not heard from them or had any confirmation for a go ahead, even after lots of phone calls to both Gordon and Rob.WW - Fri. 09/03/2001 - Does Gordon wish for the Mod to be invoiced this financial year?WW - Tue. 13/03/2001 - Gordon got back to me and said that everything was OK. He said that the nhs supplies file will be put in an intermediate directory, from where he will download it into the pharaoh directory. The files will be of the form; DDMMnhs.asc where DDMM is the day followed by the month of creation. The files will be deleted from pharaoh when they have been successfully transferred into the pharaoh database. Gordon said that everything else was OK. He will send me the signed spec. soon.WW - Wed. 21/03/2001 - Finnished and tested the mod. It consists of;nhs_sc_iss form and script in $ACLENV/com_fc_sc (This is the form)nhs_sup.awk script in $BINDIR (This is the import script to bring the ascii .csv files into pharaoh\'s nhs_sup table)enable_nhs_sc script in $PHABASE/switches (This is to enable the form and add the requesite records to the pharaoh database)nhs_sup.sql sql script in $PHABASE/sql_work (This creates the nhs_sup table required be the mod.)com main pharaoh program in $ACLENV/com (This holds the link to the new form)WW - Thu. 22/03/2001 - Sent Rob an email about the \'Quantity Issued\' being a numeric rather than a float. Tried to get hold of Gordon to talk to him about when to install next week, but he was away from the hospital today. Checked to see if the nhs_sup.awk will run with the \'#! /usr/bin/awk -f\' at the top of the script on AIX. It works fine no problems. Will need to recompile on AIX(kingtut) and just release the com.al, com.fa and com_fc_sc.fa to Gordon.WW - Tue. 27/03/2001 - will install, or at least download the mod. Still need to talk to Rob about the quantity though.KH 290301 - spoke to Gordon will download this morning and implement at lunchtime to limit disruption to users. NHS supplies installation implemented. Task Closed.WW - Mon. 17/09/2001 - Task Reopened. Gordon is finally going live with the system on 29th October. He will give me a ring about doing a test dummy run before hand. This should be done on the training database.WW - Tue. 31/12/2001 - Gordon still has not got back to me. Even after many phone calls. I will wait.KH 240402 - still awaiting testing from Gordon.KH 290402 - Gordon will contact WW this week re installed and testing this new module.WW 290402 - Gordon will contact will after 3pm today.KH 010502 - Gordon will contact will after 2.30 todayWW 020502 - Gordon will contact WW this afternoon.KH 020502 - Gordon has failed to contact WW to sort this out. Been going on for over a year now Call closed til Gordon pulls his finger out.KH 140502 - reopend to test re telephone call today. I asked him if he has tested it, he said started to but data wasn\'t going into pharaoh as a file was being overwritten, he mentioned this to WW who said would have to change something. His words! I will coordinate testing.KH 100203 - re WW, tried to get hold of Gordon but didn\'t comoe back. WW says tested and works. So task closed.', 'DEVELOPMENT - 3.6 - Item 18 - BESPOKE - An NHS Supplies mod required to transfer data into ph_spare.', 'William Wragg', 0);
