INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2409, 'James Paget Hospital NHS Trust', '2000-11-17 00:00:00', '2003-02-18 00:00:00', '1. Does not have total for WIP.2.Structure of the reports poor as have to use crystal to re-write reports to meet the criteria that matches the information thay have to extract for audit purposes etc..  They suggest two reports One grouped by cost_centre listing the assets in each costs_centre, indicating if NHS or Donated with total for  NHS, Donated and Total Then Grand Total for all cost_centres NHS, Donated, Total.  Second report is same except grouped by charge_type.KH 120301 - Email sent to Helen and Sarah requesting details of ideal report i.e. data, order and totals.KH 130301 - Email from Sarah: The charges report would best suit us if it was in cost centre order and if there was a column for \'Charges This Period\'.  Also, the layout of the report could be improved to be slightly clearer to understand at a glance. Copy of charges report sent back via email for confirmation of correct report. Sarah confirmed chgs_rep is correct report.KH 140301 - Email sent to Margery Griffin (Aintree) requesting her input to James Pagets changes. Reply to my email from Margery - will think on the matter and get back to me.KH 200301 - Email sent to Margery Griffin (Aintree) chasing response to question regarding charges report.KH 050602 - As per meeting on 300502 with Aintree and James Paget, charges repport doesn\'t contain what is need. Margery said a transaction history of each asset is need. The standard transaction report that does exist ( trans_rep) has all info but badly laid out.KH 190702 - email sent to james paget and Aintree attaching cap asset transaction report asking them to modify it to their needs.KH 220702 - email from margery with altered cap asset trans repo. Has removed transaction type code and left descript, indented 2nd and 3rd lines and brought old and new price