INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2415, 'ALL SITES', '2000-11-21 00:00:00', '2001-09-06 00:00:00', 'WW - 01/11/2000 - Wednesday - Gave Jos a very rough estimate on how long the bug2 fixes would take. (approx. 34 days).WW - 10/11/2000 - Friday - Received a fax from James Paget containing comments about the mods.WW - 13/11/2000 - Monday - Spoke to Sonia about some negative purchase orders that they had, and asked them why they had them. They had created them by creating and closing an order for 0.01 pence, and then Journalling in the negative amount (which is fine). She said that they were receipts, ie. Money being paid to them, but not credit, things like rent, and inssurance claims. I asked if a reciepts module would be good idea, and she said that it would. I spoke to Jos and he agreed.WW - 20/11/2000 - Monday - Spoke to Jos and asked him again if he would send me the list of mods.WW - 27/03/2001 - Tuesday - Tried to get hold of Bob Taylor. Spoke to Dave. He said that he would get him to ring me on Wednesday.KH 060901 - Final site (Mid Kent) upgrade. Task closed.', 'DEVELOPMENT - PHARAOH 3.6  - General', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2416, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2000-11-21 00:00:00', NULL, 'For some orders, a complete and what appears to be final invoice will come in. So they will GRN the order and close it (say \'Y\' to orderline complete). They would then get another invoice for more money against this order BEFORE they had invoiced the order. They would then invoice the order for the orginal GRN, but say no to complete the order. They would then get Sonia to sql the complete flag on the order line to \'N\' (set the line_status back to \'I\') and then raise the GRN for the additional amount that had arrived, and close the orderline again. If they did not receive further amounts, before invoicing, then they would invoice this amount and close the order.The problem now, is that if they get an additional amount BEFORE they invoice the order, but have closed the orderline, then the invoice program will NOT allow them keep the order open, it will automatically close the order. This was to stop trapped commitment.I suppose if they know about the additional order before they do the invoice then Sonia could change the complete flag to \'N\' (line_status to \'I\') at that point BEFORE they have invoiced the original GRN. The only problem with this is RED TAPE, apparently people at PWD want to see that the orderline is complete. I suppose AFTER they have invoiced the original GRN, and kept the order open, Sonia could then set the complete flag to \'Y\' (line_status to \'Y\') again, and then change it back to \'N\' (line_status to \'I\') again when they want to do the additional GRN.A code change might be to allow access on the invoice form to the complete order flag all the time, but if the orderline flag is set to complete (\'Y\') and a person chooses NOT to close the order, then the orderline complete flag could be set back to \'N\'. This would mean that they would have to have another invoice to close the order, so messages telling the user this would definitely be in order.KH 110203 - To be discusse at 190203 user group.KH 250403 - spoke to WW. New form reopn_ord1 and reopn_ord2 within Purchase Order Menu. Only reopn order that was closed in same fin year.  View same as purchase order enquiry. Will only identify order headers at status C or I.and F2 will only identify order line status C. Changing order line status to I or Y will automagically change order header status to I. Commitment will be zero.KH 010903 - WW says not doing NOW as PWD are ousting from PHARAOH. Nned explanantion in release notes.', 'DEVELOPMENT - 3.9 - They have some problems with the trapped commitment mod stopping them doing things that they used to.', 'William Wragg', 0);
