INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2461, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2000-12-15 00:00:00', '2001-02-09 00:00:00', 'WW - Looked into. SEE BELOW FOR MORE DETAILS.[activity.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated.Helen Wesley. No matter Y/N in \'Must attch job\' still attaches hours to charge_code on docket.  According to WW this problem has occurred before logged by Helen and JC explained to her that she was doing something wrong.  Will ask JC to speak to her.KH ??1200 - Helen reiterated here problem with the flag for \'Must attach job\' not working.  Spoke to JC, said he didn\'t speak to her? But said yes this was a bug.ok then.WW - Thu. 01/02/2001 - After investigation it apears that the following is happening;1) Activity codes that are flagged as have to be attached to jobs (activity.attached_to_job = \'Y\') MUST be associated with a docket number (job) in the pa_fback screen. The hours recorded against that acitivity will be charged to the charge code on the docket.2) Activity codes that are flagged as not having to be attached to jobs (activity.attached_to_job = \'N\') DO NOT have to be associated with a docket number (job) in the pa_fback screen. This is optional.      A) If the activity IS NOT associated with a docket number (job) in the pa_fback screen, then the hours recorded against that acitivity will be charged to the charge code on the activity, and NOT to the charge code on the docket. This charging will be done when another job is transferred, and depending on the day_lag variable. These activity records have a blank docket number.      B) If the activity IS associated with a docket number (job) in the pa_fback screen, then the hours recorded against that acitivity will be charged to the charge code on the docket, and NOT to the charge code on the activity.This is how the system works now, and if this is correct then no further action need be taken, except to make sure that when creating an activity code (in the \'activity\' form) which will be flagged \'Y\' as to be attached to a job, then the user should not be able to enter a charge code.If the above is incorrect then the correct way that the system should work should be spec\'ed an implemented.WW - Fri. 02/02/2001 - Spoke to Hellen, and she accepts that the description that I outlined above works, and is OK for her purposes, and she can use the financial reports to get the info from the blank docketed hours worked records. These will get transferred to history when a docket gets transferred, and the record is outside the day lag range.', 'BUG2 - AO - Performance module Activity code not attached to correct charge code', 'Kate Hamilton', 1);
