INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2501, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2001-02-09 00:00:00', '2001-01-12 00:00:00', 'logged by Diane.  Dialed in. Quite a few users logged into system but not in Capital Charging.  Told Diane then Margery user maybe be locking table indirectly, suggested getting gall uisers off system to clear any locks instead og trying to kill the locks off. >locks diplayed ca_dets locked by Margery. Margey will try again end of day, or Monday morning after backup as hasn\'t done one. Call closed.KH 120201 =- Call reopened. Margery unable to run period end again due to database lock.  Uable to dial into their database as firewall in effect and we don\'t have have an account yet.  Irene Smith of IT gave us temporary dial in but meant required software we don\'t have.  Talked Margery through process of identifying processes running ps -ef | grep \'username\' and kill them. Got her to shutdowen databases then start period end. Worked. Call closed.', 'Error message unable to lock ca_dets when trying to run charges period end.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2502, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2001-02-13 00:00:00', '2001-02-16 00:00:00', 'Call lgged by Gordon Fotheringham. Last time JC was up there he advised Gordon to bring codes in line with the finance dept. When change management_unit in cost_centre maintenance asset_id man_unit does not update automatically.  Told him would have to manually go through every asset and reselect the cost_centre so that new man_unit is displayed. He said has 8000 assets. Told him I not to do anything will look into a solution.  WW said would take a few days to check code and produce procedure to ensure all nases covered, they will have to be charged.  I will speak to JC tomorrow (wed 14 Feb) morning to discuss.KH 140201 - Spoke to Gordon. He said will physically update each asset (6500) with new cost_centre, has already started.  Suggested a possible easier way.  WW spoke to JC for clarification on matter as changing management_unit associated with cost_centre and updating asset with it may have serious repercussions. JC denies suggesting bring Pharaoh codes into alignment with finance, he will speak to Gordon.KH 160201 - JC spoke to Gordon yesterday.  Should have been creating new codes not amending old ones. Has done that now, tuned out he couldn\'t update the changes he hd made so no damage done. Call closed.', 'Assets not updated with new information when management_unit unit related to cost_centre changed.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
