INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2505, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2001-02-20 00:00:00', '2001-02-20 00:00:00', 'The table is ca_dets, and the fields, are management_unit, cost_centre, and net_book_val_fld. The net_book_val_fld wants to be subtotalled by cost_centre. The correct SQL is as follows;select management_unit,           cost_centre,          sum(net_book_val_fld)from ca_detsgroup by management_unit, cost_centre;With out the grouping the sum( ) will return an error. A HAVING clause, or a WHERE clause would work just as well.', 'Margery is trying to do an SQL query whereby the result will be grouped and subtotalled.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2506, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2001-02-20 00:00:00', '2001-02-23 00:00:00', 'It turns out that the chgs_rep gets the interest rates, both the CI and HI, from the int_rates table before going onto do anything, and if it can\'t find them then the form backs out. The interest rates are held by financial year, and the chgs_rep gets the interests rates for the current financial year (curr_fin_year.control) which is held in the control file. This IS NOT THE CAPITAL CHARGES year. Margery had only a CI record, and not the additional required HI record for the financial year referenced by her control file, \'1999\'. She added the record, and will test some time today.KH 230201 - Haven\'t heard from Margery assume went ok. Call closed.', 'Margery gets an error when she tries to do a capital charges period end. The error message is something about \'..missing interest rates ..\'', 'William Wragg', 0);
