INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2514, 'Tower Hamlets Healthcare Trust', '2001-02-23 00:00:00', '2001-03-01 00:00:00', 'Call loggeb by Steve Royce. WW took call. Dialed in. hasn\'t had a decent backup since 22 Dec 2000. On 25Dec2000 system unable to write to backup device so could be hardware, but he hasn\'t been checking his backups.  Dialed on. Live db may be corrupted. KH shutdown all databases and made copy (data, data.city,data.cityold, data.newham, data.train) to /backup.  Backed up all databases onto tape, after chexking tape drive works. Ran diagnostics to file kate. File showed no corruption just two overloaded table. Sent e-mail to Steve Royce informing him diagnostics was good. To check his backup first thing and if ok, ok to go in.WW - Mon. 26/02/2001 - Kate said that everything was OK, so call closed. Kate has asked Steve to do a full system backup, root & Boot.KH 270201 - Call reopened.  Backup failed last night as user still logged in and couln\'t read device. Steve has confirmed is using DDS3.  Informed me via e-mail that new cleaning tape arrived and now green light has stopped flashing. Dialed in backup for Friday puzzleing as it appears it didn\'t actually write to the tape.  Tonight new tapes are beng used and Steve has sressed to the user to be logged out when they leave. Call closed.KH 280201 - Call reopened. E-mail received from steve Royce saying backup states differences in read/write. Dialed on backup has not written to tape, couldn\'t open.  WW and I will attempt to manuall y backup data.newham.Running the backup from cron rescheduled. Backup successfully wrote to tape, although backup is dud as rogue process inhibited shutdown. Replaced their backup programs with ours. Steve will e-mail tomorrow morning with results of tonights backup.KH 010301 - Checked with Steve Royce if backup successful.  He voiced over phone results but asked that I dial into to check he is rea