INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2553, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-03-23 00:00:00', '2001-03-26 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Helen Wesley.  During current fin year new management_units created and curr ones deleted. Records were altered accordingly but budget reocrds can not be changed.  Current fin year had approx 500 budget records. Create next years budget only created 170 records.  Spoke to JC he said create next years budget creates a zero budget record for every records in current fin year, will have to manually create budget records for new management units.  JC is does not know why program would fall over with said message. Recent modification should have allowed process to skip duplicates and continue. 3.15pm spoke to Helen informed her what JC had said to me, told I will speak to WW re this Modification to see if BUG exists.  Will speak to her again on Monday.KH 260301 - spoke to WW then Helen. 3 options available - Option1: Allow old budgets to continue next year a fizzle out and leave history instatct. Option 2: Cancel orders with no GRNS, bring in dummy invoices for 0.01p on orders with grns and create credit notes for -0.01p, then  re-order on new budget next year, linking budgets by doing a variatin order. Option 3: We manually change the management unit to new code on all relevant budgets (approx 300) which will be time consuming, expensive and result in loss of data integrity NOT recommended. Helen will go for option 3. Call closed.', 'Create next years budget fell over with message: reocrd already exists.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
