INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2555, 'Tower Hamlets Healthcare Trust', '2001-03-26 00:00:00', '2001-03-30 00:00:00', 'Call logged by Steve Royce. Has modified order status from I to C and system shows this but crystal report still shows status C. PO no 297800 has been modified to status C but still shows as I.Order number 298000 has one line which is status I, asked Steve to try to modify the status again as shouldn\'t be inhibiting, he did and was successful. Order 297800 has 28 grn_dets records, all 28 have been invoiced. 7 ol_dets records 3 of which are line_status Y. 4885/4 4885/5 4885/6.  Order 298200has 20 grn_dets records, all 20 have been invoiced. 5 ol_dets records 1 of which are line_status Y. 4891/3. Steve will find out the exact numbe of these cases and get back to us.  When he does will have to manually change the line_status to I via SQL so that he can close the orders.  According to WW if too many he will be charged.KH 280301 - Steve phoned with other problem but mentioned approximate number of trapped commits maybe in excess of 100. Told him Datapro were prepared to do a one off fix but need to know exactly how many and a list of the order numbers and line numbers that have trapped commitment.KH 290301 - Steve not in today due to strike. Spoke to Roger Brooks (his colleague) will get Steve to try and provide list of orders with trapped grn\'s to us electronically tomorrow. He\'s due to run Year end on Saturday.KH 300301 - Steve called to say will get list of orders with trapped commitments to me within the hour.  10.50am Steve called to say forget it.  Too many other problems to worry about, will get users to manually close off outstanding orders that can. Call closed.', 'Unable to complete outstanding invoices.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
