INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2562, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2001-03-30 00:00:00', '2001-08-20 00:00:00', 'TO BE INSTALLED (with pharaoh 3.6) INSTALLED[mv_bu_rec.fq/fs/rp]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[proj_zm.fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[account_zm.fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put,  .changes ammended[cost_ct_zm.fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put,  .changes ammended[pj_dets.fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammendedRequested by Sonia McIntosh.E-mail sent to sonia informing her that we will not be assisting as do not approve of data manipulation via SQL, but to use SQLs we provided last if still intend to do so. Copy of e-mail sent to WW, KS and BK.(Morning SoniaWith regard to your request for a repeat procedure of last years Account Code changes,  we do not condone this form of data conversion and therefore will not be assisting in its implementation.  To enforce data integrity we suggest closure of the old accounts and creation of new ones.  Last year we did stipulate that our assistance was a one off and was reassured by yourselves that the request would not be raised again.If you intend to pursue this method of data manipulation the procedure is the same as last year and so you should use the SQLs provided at that time.Apologies for any inconvenience.RegardsKate HamiltonPharaoh SupportDataPro Software Ltd)email from Sonia saying not satisfied with our answer, should support there policy. BK to speak with her  confirming we will support them if the use the system correctly.WW - Mon. 02/04/2001 - Went to see Sonia, with Keith, and talk about what to do about the account code changes. Decided to create a program that will move a budget. Required by Mon. 09/04/2001.WW - Fri. 06/04/2001 - Finnished, testing and codeing new budget movement form - mv_bu_rec. Packaged it up to send over the modem to