INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2565, 'Royal Dundee Liff Hospital', '2001-04-02 00:00:00', '2001-04-04 00:00:00', 'Calll logged by Glynnis Watt.When feeding back docket (176905,200404,198084). According to Friday nights backup diagnostics show many corruptions.  Dialled in, Friday nights back show index corruptions on 4 tqables (ph_hist, ph_w_don, ph_j_det and job_audt) Thursday nights back shows same corruption.  File.err doesn\'t indicate system shutdown however ??? Does state system rebooted at 15:07. Thuesday and Wednesday night backup failed as SQL processes still running when try to shutdown databases.  Told Glynnis \'FAILED TO CHECK BACKUP\' and may have to restore from last good backup which is Monday 26March. She\'s non too happy about this, I say I will try and fix corrupted yables which means system will be down for rest of today and good part of tomorrow. She prepared for this.Ran dbdump ph_hist in subs but had to kill processes as ran out of room. MB created new filesystem called /dump with 480Mb, set dbdump ph_hist off again sending ti /dump: dbdump -d /dump ph_hist.dumped data and schema for all tables abd dropped and rebuilt and dbloaded them, MB finished dbload from home.  KH 030401 - Last nights backup went ok but diagnostics still shows error. Hole detected at offset, re WW ran: $UNIFY/../diag/volchk -Oreorganize > kate to fix original corruption, DEFRAG.  Told Glynnis to inform us of any errors immediately and make sure gets good backup up tonight. Call closed.MB 040401 - Call reopened. Call from Glynnis, last nights backup show index corruptions for cw_job, error log doean\'t indicate reason. KH dialed in a repaired table cw_job. Call closed.', 'DBERROR inserting in ph_w_don status = -12  DBERROR inserting into ph_j_dets status = -12', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
