INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2586, 'ALL SITES', '2001-04-18 00:00:00', '2001-06-21 00:00:00', '[rais_appr2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[purch_req2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[val_purch2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[auth_reqs2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[amend_ord2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[pord_enq2.fq/fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[ids_deafaults.h]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[$PHABASE/upgrade.360/ol_dets.upd]: created, tested, README.360 updatedItem 8:=======Is an additional field required on the orderlines, to take the VAT value? This would be similar to the invoice screen, where the total including VAT is given in the total value field, and then a separate field holds the amount of the total which is VAT e.g.Total amount = 117.50Total VAT = 17.50So the total without VAT would be 100.00This would be consistent with how the rest of Pharaoh handles VAT, and would allow variable VAT amounts. If this is not what is required, and instead VAT is to be added to the amount automatically, then please let me know specifics.The above was sent as an email (on Mon 12/03/2001) to Bob Taylor (East Kent Community Healthcare NHS Trust) to get his feedback, as arranged at the user group meeting. I have not heard back from him yet. I have phoned and left messages a number of times to no avail.WW - Mon. 21/05/2001 - Doing the above.', 'DEVELOPMENT - 3.6 - Item 8 - Provide a facility on Purchase Order line for entering VAT.', 'William Wragg', 0);
