INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2708, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2001-08-20 00:00:00', '2001-08-29 00:00:00', '[purch_req2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[val_purch2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[rais_appr2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[amend_ord2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[goods_rec2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[purch_inv.fs]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[purch_inv2.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updated[purch_inv3.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes updatedPWD raise an order for a project. They then raise and invoice GRN\'s against that order. If the project increases in value they raise a variation order against the original order, to show thw increase. When they bring in the final invoice for the project they use this to close the original order. They seem to ignore the variation order! They then wish to close the variation order, so raise a GRN, and then bring in an invoice for 1 penny. They then on the third screen zero that value and close the order. So the invoice value vanishes!!! They can nolonger do this, as I fixed that bug. If they allocate in the second screen a value of 1 penny, then that is how much must be the value before closing the order.The solution seems to me and Jos to be as follows;When they bring in the final invoice for the project, instead of just closing the originally order with it, they should also close any variation order/s at the same time. Even if they only allocate a single penny to the variation order/s this will be a penny that does NOT vanish, but is accounted for!When they phone back, this is what I will say to them.WW - Fri. 24/08/2001 - Spoken to Keith and Sonia, the solution we have come up with is as follows;(1) Allow zero purchase orders to be raised.(2) Allow zero invoices to be raised.(3) Allow zero invoices to be paid.', 'Cannot zero an allocated value on the third invoice screen!', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2711, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-08-20 00:00:00', '2001-08-30 00:00:00', '[pa_fback.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.error is in the \'field docket_number\' section;field docket number...        if pa_fback:$docket_number <> \'\' then        begin /*{*/            set    dummy_ls to            select cw_job.docket_no            from   cw_job            where  cw_job.docket_no = pa_fback:$docket_number            and   status_flag in (\'1\',\'2\',\'3\',\'8\');            if status$() = 0 then            begin /*{*/                beep$(1)                display \' The Docket Number entered does not\'+                        \' exist as Current Work.\'                    for fyi_message wait                restart on field            end   /*}*/        end   /*}*/.... The above should give one of two separate error messages;1) that the docket number is not in the current work file or is at status \'8\'                                               OR2) that the docket number is in the current work file but is not a status \'4\' or \'6\'.', 'When in pa_fback and a user enters an invalid docket number, or a docket number which has already been fedback then the system used to tell the user that the docket did not exist in current work.', 'William Wragg', 1);
