INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2736, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2001-09-04 00:00:00', '2003-02-11 00:00:00', 'Logged by Sonia. Plus batch reporting filenames currently ar 000000PWD would need to be 000000PCD plus doc type maintenance. Sonia will email me file containing filenames.KH 070901 - WW in communication.WW - Wed. 05/09/2001 - (1) Putting the database on the super menu is no problem.(2) The \'PWD\' in the ac_output report is hard coded into the report itself. This would not be hugely difficult to change so that if \'PDC\'(?) was running the report then that would come out, and if \'PWD\' then that would come out. It would mean some code changes though, probably about a days work - off the top of my head.(3) The GRN date inclusion should also be no problem. Again this would require some code changes, probably about two days work.If (2) and (3) could be done together this would obviously save some work :o)WW - Wed. 12/09/2001 - Mike Moone rang me about the possibility of allowing the projects to have multiple charge codes, so that when a PO is raised with a project code, the charge code can be picked up from the a list of assigned charge codes for that project. He wishes to know if this is possible, and roughly what the cost will be.WW - Tues. 18/09/2001 - Results from \"Multiple account codes for one project\";(a) Use the pj_dets screen to add the multiple account codes by:      (1) make a new key on pj_dets so that project codes can be duplicated. This will than allow a project to be set up with multiple account codes - the project_code/account_code combination will be unique, these will be the fields used for the new key and will need to be checked when a user enters them.      (2) create the f7-f7 duplicate but don\'t store feature to allow the easy creation of multiple account code associations. Possibly do a different way though.(b) There needs to be a zoom form created for rais_appr2, purch_req2, val_purch2 and amend_ord2 which allows the selection of the account codes associated with a project code to be selected from.Speak to Jos about the above and see if he thinks it\'s a bad idea or not. Kieth say this is a good thing. It will take about approximately (if everything goes smoothly) 5 days. Speak the Mike Moone.Spoke to Mike Moone about the above and the additional changes Sonia mentioned. They will probably not be requiring the GRN date stuff, but will probably be going with the project change and the accounts transfer changes (these will require a new report and form). We said subject to speccing between 10-20 days work.KH 110203 - WW says was to do with bringing in new management unit but didn\'t. Closed.', 'BESPOKE - WAITING - Want blank database to appear on super menu + other Mods.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
