INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2754, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2001-09-06 00:00:00', '2002-02-11 00:00:00', 'logged by Diane. When relocating capital asset cost centre. Tried it myself with asset 9196 worked fine. Asked Joan to try again.KH 130901 - Spoke to Joan, more cap assets unable to relocate with same error message 23501, 21934, 7513, 7890, 873. According to Joan all captial assets have blank division.KH 180901 - able to have blank division when create management unit with no division though was able to successfully relate asset using this.( bearing in mind not effective till april 2002 as period end has been run into future, not sure if this will affect it). Will have to dial on to their system to do more testing.KH 240901 - Diane will fax throught example to try. Tried to dial on but unsuccesful, Aintree to come back.KH  250901 - Dial on and tested relocation of cap asst, got error message. Looked at code and can see no reason why. Spoke to Joan, she will do fresh backup and send us the tape so that can replicate problem here.KH 280901 - tape received.KH 041001 - Seconded to other project will have to postpone loading of data onto scodev.KH 151001 - Call from Sarah at James Paget, getting same error message when relocating asset. Does not have blank divions.KH 261001 - Sarah at James Paget Phoned re task, said needs attentin as wrong departments being charged.KH 291001 - Aintree database loaded into SCODEV.Successfully relocated some assets that Joan had given me. Spoke to Margery who will get Diane to phone me tomorrow with some ore.KH 301001 - Diane phone but said Joan has list of problems ones but on leave this week.. Will have a look but may have to wait till next week.KH 110201 - difference of either division/management_unit/cost_centre/account code between ca_dets screen and ap_dets (apportionements) causes relocation to failed. Told Diane/Joan to make sure all apportionm