INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2763, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2001-09-20 00:00:00', '2001-09-26 00:00:00', 'Phil has installed Multiveiw 2000 version 6.0.5 and then the pharoh JSB 1.4.4 He has then set the correct ip address for the server. He can ping the server ok. He can telnet to the server with Multiview and tinyterm. The problem is that when he runs the pharaoh.zzt file it loads the background image but then stops, it does not bring up the server login prompt. He has unistalled the Multiview 2000 and then reinstalled. He has then reinstalled the pharaoh JSB 1.4.4 from the pharaoh 3.6 CD, but the same thing happens. He has tried running the pharaoh.zzt from within a Multiveiw 2000 screen, but the same thing happens. He has installed the same Multiview 2000 version 6.0.5 on two other machines, along with the pharaoh JSB 1.4.4 with no problems. We have no problems with the pharaoh.zzt at this end either. The other two were installed on windows 98 machines, and this one is a windows 95 machine. Does this make a difference? I have installed 6.0.5 on a windows 95 machine here along with pharaoh JSB 1.4.4 and it works fine.I have sent Multiview support an email.WW - Mon. 24/09/2001 - spoke to Adam from their support department, and he said that I should try creating a blank .ZZT file and then copying individually the separate config files embeded in the pharaoh.ZZT into the blank one. Phoned Phil and asked him to give this ago. He will try it tomorrow morning.WW - Tue. 25/09/2001 - Phil did  as Adam suggested on the phone - blank .ZZT, then bring in each of the config files separately - it turns out that it is the multiView2000 font. When this is selected all text disappears? As this is the font I selected in the .ZZT file to keep consistency, no login message appears and the prompt just seems to sit on a blank screen. Phil is going to load Win 98 on the machine, as the courier font just doesn\'t work properly, no box drawin. This is possibly to do with unicode support or lack of. Sent Adam an email mentioning the above. Call closed until further notice.', 'Cannot get the JSB Pharaoh 1.4.4 running.', 'William Wragg', 0);
