INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2767, 'Eastbourne General District Hospital', '2001-09-26 00:00:00', '2001-10-23 00:00:00', 'logged by Brian. If select individual job type ie Project report displays no data though definitely is. But if select all job types gives all jobs including job type project. WW looked and report code, appears searches done on a requested date for which some jobs especially PM jobs don\'t, so problem with report. Can\'t just remove search for a requested date as don\'t now if need for other job types. Will asks users and check spec. No spec will speak to JC.KH 280901 - spoke to JC, said no important reason why date_requested should be removed in search criteria with code for pm jobs. Emailled change spec to 15 sites asking for queries in before Friday 5 October. 2 hard copies sent via to 2 sites as have no email. Spec proposes removing date_requested from code search criteria totally.KH 021001 - re-emailed RDE and Glenfield as their mail was returned. RDE returned again, alternative email provided by Trevor till gets his new one.KH 041001 - 4 sites (Barts&London, Eastbourne, East Kent and Redbridge) represented and User group meeeting at SCO/Calder on 3 Oct agreed to Spec.KH 161001 - date_requested in ph_hist is date_to_com_ex.  Added SQL to set date_to_comp_ex to date from wk_nums that matches week_planned for PPM jobs.KH 221001 - finished editing ph_jbcmp and tested ok. Will test again tomorrow before putting.KH 231001 - report tested and put. Task closed. Will get new version with next patch/upgrade/release.', 'ph_jbcmp report not displaying information when should.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2768, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-09-27 00:00:00', '2002-02-13 00:00:00', 'This happens occassionally, and does not seem to have any affect on the data.The error is not bad. It happens if there are some spares to be transferred but no hours worked records for a docket. The count_ln variable should be set to zero at line 1375, so that when on line 1424 where count_ln is checked to see if there were any records (count_ln > 0) it will only delete when there were records. At the moment the count_ln variable is counting BOTH the spares records AND the hrs_wrkd records!!!! This need to be fixed.KH 120202 - in form tr_to_hist added in line 1383: set $count_ln to 0. Tested and transfer to history worked without errors. Forms pa_fb1 and dckt_fack already have the line. Will test agin tomorrow.KH 130202 - added stock to dockt 124. (has no hrs worked) feedback and ran transfer to history. No error. Form put. Task closed.', 'BUG3 - When transferring to history get an dberror -35 deleting hrs_wrkd.', 'William Wragg', 1);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2769, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2001-09-27 00:00:00', '2002-03-05 00:00:00', 'Gordon is posting an example to us of the overunning fault dockets and the non fault dockets.WW - Mon. 15/10/2001 - Gordon will be taking them to the user group meeting, to show Brian. Hopefully he will bring them back down here.WW - Fri. 19/10/2001 - Spoke to Gordon, I will dial on Mon. 22nd and have a look at his docket printing report.WW - Fri. 26/10/2001 - I have got his docket it is in com_ao_cw/reports and called tay_jd.rp It will need to be entered into SCCS when it is complete. Brian said that it will be chargable, he will be speaking to Gordon about it.WW - Thu. 22/11/2001 - arranged to dial in at 1.30 to upload the test job docket and get him to print it out, and say how well it fits on the paper.WW - Fri. 23/11/2001 - He could not manage today, so will be doing it on Mon. 26th at 1.30 instead.WW - Tue. 04/12/01 - Spoken to Gordon and finally got him to print out the test page. They don\'t fit, he can\'t have 3 dockets to a page, unless he can chnage the font size or margins, which he says he cannot do. I said that mid January we could try out the windows printing which will be able to set the font size. I the mean time, I have amended his docket \'tay_jd.rp\' so that it it pages after each docket, this way he will be able to print ranges of dockets without having to print each one out seperately. It is still a waste of paper though.WW - Tue. 05/03/2002 - Recieved examples of Gordons double page dockets a week or so ago. I have ammended the \'tay_jd.rp\' docket so that it will print two dockets per page, and page at the right times. Gordon will ring me between 2 and 3 today for me to download the new docket, and for him to test it. All works now, call closed.', 'When printing fault dockets (3 to a laser A4 page) the last docket slightly overuns the end and co