INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2771, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2001-10-02 00:00:00', '2001-11-15 00:00:00', 'NEED TO ADD cw_job.time_reported INTO ph_hist because of the reason below.KH 031001 - spoke to Phil at user group meeting at SCO/Caldera. Using crystal reports on ph_hist, info coming out is \"way off\" when relates to small time elapse, but large reponses times are \"spot on\".KH 041001 - Fax received from Phil detailing report criteria and copy of results.WW - Thu. 18/10/2001 - It turns out that the ph_hist.tot_hrs_resp is accurate. It calculates this by using the following fields;REPORTED DATE: cw_job.date_reportedREPORTED TIME: cw_job.time_reportedRESPONDED DATE: cw_job.data_act_respRESPONDED TIME: cw_job.time_respA client can have the modify date & time (control.mod_date_time) set to \'Y\' to enable them to modify the reported date and time, when a fault job is first created. The time repoted is NOT sent to history! Only the log_time is sent. The log_time is the time that the fault record was created. If the user does not change the reported time, these will be practically the same. Phil was thinking the log_time was the time that the fault was reported, and so when he used this time to manually work out the total hours to respond, he got some that didn\'t tally with Pharaoh\'s calculations. These were the ones where the time_reported had been altered on the fault report. He will drop the log_time from his report. The time_reported should be taken across into ph_hist as well. This will be done in pharaoh 3.7KH 311001 - added new fields and modifications made to, cw_job, ph_hist.KH 141101 - completed modifications to dckt_fback, pa_fb1 and tr_to_hist. Tested ok.KH 151101 - WW tested, further modifications and scripts put. Task closed.', 'BUG3 - Report on hours response showing up incorrect on some eg: 12:10 reported Responded at 17:00 shows 10min response. Some others show up correct.', 'Mike Bloomfield', 1);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2773, 'Royal Devon & Exeter Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-10-03 00:00:00', '2001-10-08 00:00:00', 'Bob has linked;cc_phist ---- docket_number/docket_no ----> ph_hist ---- perm_history_id/job_dets_id ----> ph_j_det                                                                            |                                                                            \'---------- asset_id -----------------------------------> as_detsThe criteria used for the cc_phist table are;name, entered_date, activity_codeThe returned information is;cc_phist.hours, ph_j_det.detail1 etc.., as_dets.asset_nameThe report works for records before 25th May, but not after.Bob created a report with just the cc_phist table and nothing else, with no criteria. He did\'nt get anything after the 25th of May. Fiona reconds it might be the row limit set in crystal. As crystal brings in all the records first for each table, then if the table is larger than the size set it will only bring in the first records from the table upto that value. The setting is in, File ----> Properties ----> reporting(TAB) ----> untick the count rows setting. I have asked Bob to try this, and if it doesn\'t work to send me both the original report, and the one with just the cc_phist table in it, on a floppy disc. It didn\'t work so he is sending me the reports on floppy.KH 081001 - Disk received. Report looks fine, dialled on to their system, according to cc_phist ASTILL. J. has no records since 24 May 2001. Bob looked closer at his criteria and realised problem lied with name change to ASTILL J. task closed.', 'Crystal reports problem. Problem with a report which will return information before 25th May but nothing after.', 'William Wragg', 0);
