INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2813, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '2002-02-08 00:00:00', 'Phil is having a slight problem whilst printing his PPM on Wednesday mornings. The problem that occurs is that whilst the user eddie has started to print the PPM, whilst this is happening it appears to prevent all the other users from saving new or amended records. However once he finishes and logs off everything returns to normal. Phil wants to know how he can overcome this.I sent Phil the following reply by email:<snip>How many jobs get printed? If it is greater than 100 then the whole of the cw_job table gets locked, so no one can do anything with respect to that table until it is unlocked. If you can give me a max number of jobs that get printed in one print run, and an average, I can adjust your database settings to not lock the entire table below this level. The reason that a whole table is locked, is to speed things up, as if every record in a large table is locked then this can cause a noticeable slowdown. If people try to alter one of the jobs which is being printed out, they will still not be able to until the batch has been printed. There is nothing I can do about that I\'m afraid.<snip>I shall wait to find out what the reply is. I will then amend the LMPROMO varaible in the file.cf file in there live database to reflect the new required table locking level. It is currently set to 100, as mentioned in my email.He got back to me saying that there are less than 100 per batch, but eddie stays in the screen and does not come out. He will try coming out of the screen after each batch and see if that helps.WW - Tue. 13/11/2001 - I have heard nothing, so I am assuming that coming out of the form and then going back in again did the trick. This should be changed in 3.7 so that a person can stay in the form and do additional prints, freeing up the previously locked records.KH 160102 - Added unlock cw_job; to end of field section rep_option_ss in jd_print. Still locking though.KH 170102 - added unlock control;.KH 310102 -  added COMMIT WORK; at end of rep_option_ss field. Transferred 10 weeks from planned main to cw and printed lot. After run finished kept sceeen open and ran locks on another telnet session. No locks appears. Check was able to update cw job that had just been print. I could. Task closed.WW - Wed. 06/02/2002 - Kate you also need unlock add_inf.KH 080202 - added unlock add_inf at end of rep_option_ss. Task closed.', 'BUG3 - Job docket printing - locking problems.', 'William Wragg', 1);
