INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2822, 'Royal Dundee Liff Hospital', '2001-11-23 00:00:00', '2001-11-23 00:00:00', 'They have tried using pord_enq to view the order but it does not show up.The order is in the database, but the order header has an order_status of \'V\' and does not have the authorised_ref, or date_authorised set? The order lines all have status \'I\' and the fx_dets records for each order line have been written. Eric said that a user was in that order when it was printed. He might have been authorising whne it was printed? Anyway I have updated the oh_dets.order_status to \'I\', the oh_dets. authorised_ref to \'pete\' and the oh_dets.date_authorised to 22/11/2001. Everything else seems to have been done for the order except these.', 'An order has been printed \'2628100\' but cannot been seen.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2823, 'Northampton Community Healthcare NHS Trust', '2001-11-23 00:00:00', '2002-04-16 00:00:00', 'logged by Barry Steele. Last line closed or cancelled should close header but not to have done it in three cases. Order number 227200, 259200, 283600.WW - Spoke to Barry Steele. The problem isn\'t urgent, and comes from the time when they were starting to use the order system. The problem is that all the order lines are either closed \'C\' or cancelled \'X\', but the order header is still open \'I\'. It probably has something to do with cancelling some order lines and bringing invoices in against some others, some where the order header does not get closed. Possibly some of the lines are invoiced, but the rest are cancelled, and perhaps the amend_order program does not closed order headers when there are closed lines against it?WW - Mon. 15/04/2002 - I think the best course of action is to for each order pick an order line which is status \'Y\' and set it back to \'I\' and then close it with a 0.00 invoice. I will have to have a look at there system to see eactly what the probelm is, and figure out a specific solution. If all the order lines are closed, then I think it should just be acase of SQLing the header closed.There were 26 order headers which had the problem. The orders headers were status \'I\' while the order lines were either \'C\', \'X\', or \'Y\'. This is the trapped commitment problem. Solution: SQL the order lines with status of \'Y\' to a status of \'I\' and then use modify order status to change the status of the order header to \'C\' by changing the order line status to \'C\'. SQL to do the order line update:update ol_dets set line_status = \'I\'where order_number IN (   select order_number from oh_dets   where order_status = \'I\')and line_status = \'Y\';The modify order statsu form can be found in:Financial control --> General maintenance menu --> Modify order status.I have done the SQL and left a message with Barry to get back to me tomorrow morning so that I can explain to him what needs to be done.WW - Tue. 16/04/2002 - Spoke with Barry, explained to him what needs to be done. He understands and will go ahead with it. He will ring me if he has any problems.', 'Order header open where all order lines either closed or cancelled.', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2824, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2001-11-26 00:00:00', '2002-01-11 00:00:00', 'The project number is 553476The order is 6499600There is another order with a 200000 NVO against it the NVO order is 6639401 The problem is a bug within the prj_choice report form. The nvo_total_est_cost_la variable is only reset to 0.00 when a closed order comes along, if the order is still open the variable keeps it\'s value. The varaible needs to be reset when an original order on its first order line comes along with a status of \'I\'. This will stop an NVO against a still open original order being added to a different closed order.WW - Thu. 29/11/2001 - Installed and tested again by Mike, everything looks ok. I will put the change tomorrow.WW - Wed. 05/12/2001 - The pj_dets form still has a problem with calculation of the outstanding commitment.WW - Mon. 31/12/2001 - Changed the section between the XXXXXXX\'s on the pj_dets form to reflect the changes which I made to the prj_choice form. The oustanding commitment calculation seems to work fine now. I will send the change to PWD after the New Year.WW - Fri. 11/01/2002 - Done. Works fine.', 'Project details is showing a closed order with 200000 commitment against it, even  though it should have 0.00 The total estimated cost entered was only 10,000 and no where in any of the transactions is 200000 mentioned?', 'William Wragg', 1);
