INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2850, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2002-01-02 00:00:00', '2002-03-20 00:00:00', '[rais_appr2.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[purch_req2.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[val_purch2.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[ass_and_pr.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[iss_and_pr.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.The order, VO, commitment, and expenditure are as follows:Original Order: 6633400 for 5000.00 - expenditure 5287.00Variation Order: 6633401 for 2000.00 - expenditure 0.00The negative VO tried was for -1000.000. This should be OK. as the VO + the orignal order still have more than 1000.00 oustanding. If the code only uses the original order need to find out why it was that way rather than also taking into account the VO\'s.The code does only use the original orders commitment. I think we did it this way as the negative VO was to vary the original orders commitment and not any VO\'s commitment. I will look into the negative VO\'s using the original orders commitment values as well as any VO\'s that are brought against it for 3.7. In the mean time Sonia will have to cancel VO\'s and re-input them for a lesser value, this is not so bad as all payments are against the original order - the VO\'s get closed at 0.00.', 'DEVELOPMENT - 3.7 - A negative VO is trying to be raised against an original order which also has a VO against it, but the system comes back saying that the original order no longer has any outstanding commitment against it.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2851, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2002-01-02 00:00:00', '2002-01-03 00:00:00', 'The onscreen value from pj_dets is fine.WW - Thu. 03/02/2002 - The problem stems from the very large purchase order within the project (2956400) it was closed on 03/12/2001 which meant that the expenditure would be shown as the commitment on the report. The expenditure was over 42,000,000 and the input section of the report was setting the commitment_la variable to an [amount 8]. This has been changed now to an [amount 10] and everything works fine now.I have changed our reports and PWD\'s. Sonia will test to see if everything is OK.', 'Stars are appearing in the total commitment for the large project 504681, when it is printed out from prj_choice.', 'William Wragg', 0);
