INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2854, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2002-01-07 00:00:00', '2003-11-17 00:00:00', 'On SCO the following files and directories need to be mirrored on the two systems to keep the users passwords insync:/tcb (dir)/etc/auth (dir)/etc/passwd (file)/etc/default/passwd (file)/etc/profile (file)the directories and files need to keep their attributes. To make sure that this happens then the above filenames and directories (all the filenames in the directories as well as the directory names themselves)need to be put into a file - each filename on a seperate line - and then used with the cpio command to create a cpio file. This cpio file then needs to be rcp\'d across to the other machine and then uncpio\'d.(1) cat filelist | cpio -oBvc > rcpfile(2) rcp rcpfile <remote machine>(3) rcmd cpio -oBvcdum < rcpfile (could do instead on the backup machine when it is about to be used)(stage three is done from the live machine as a remote command)The users home directories need to be taken across as well, but I think the current rcp setup already does that.WW - Thu. 10/10/2002 - They are moving to Linux, different files need to be copied across.ON HOLD', 'PWD tested the backup system, and discovered that the user\'s passwrds were not taken across.', 'William Wragg', 0);
