INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2862, 'Parliamentary Works Directorate', '2002-01-17 00:00:00', '2002-01-22 00:00:00', 'Sonia wants to be able to change the\'management unit\' as well as the \'cost centre\' and \'account code\'. I will look into it to see if the screen can be changed easily. She wants to be able to JUST change the \'management unit\' and leave the \'cost centre\' and \'account code\' the same.WW - Mon. 21/01/2002 - Sent Sonia an email, requesting more info.WW - Tue. 22/01/2002 - Got an email from Sonia, but need to speak to her as I still need more info. I will recommend, depending on the additional info which I get, the following;(1) Sonia creates next and future year budgets with the correct management unit, or if they are already created changes them with SQL JUST AFTER THE YEAR END.(2) JUST AFTER THE YEAR END Sonia then SQL\'s all the projects with the wrong management unit to the correct one.Any other method will require lots of work to figure out, and then the result might be that it messes the data up to much and data integrity is lost. Spoke to Sonia and told her the above, she said she is happy with that and will go ahead with that.', 'Change to the budget movement screen requested.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2863, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2002-01-18 00:00:00', '2002-01-28 00:00:00', 'Phil Turner (not Lewis) 0207 3777150WW - Fri. 18/01/2002 - spoke to Unify and sent them many emails, waiting to hear back from them with some sort of a solution. I am dumping the data from the live database, as I have a hunch that the error is due to one of the volumes being full up. Here is the text of the last email that I sent to Unify;Hi Ray,>I have notice in your schema that although you have data is scattered turned on you do not have Volume 5 in the to use List ?The vol5 is not in the schema I sent you as that volume was added after the database was created, around the beginning of August 2001 using the ALTER TABLE sql statement. The vol5 is in the \'dummpdd\' of the tables as the database now stands.>and all the other volumes are full.The only volume which is full is vol1. vol1 - vol5 are preallocated 100mb files.>is this \"script\" run every day ?? and therefore this the first day you have had trouble? Did you create Volume 5 this morning ?Yes and Yes>Have you tried inserting records manually (Interactive SQL?) and seen if they go into Volume 5 without giving you the error ?I can add via SQL records to ph_hist. I tested entering 4 records.I was speaking to the user and they said that some records were transferred, and when he tried it again another record was transferred before the error.Can I make a hypothesis? The scattering algorithm uses some form of random distribution, but does not remove full volumes from it\'s volume list. Hence the fact that some records can be entered but then a user will get a -99 error. Does this sound plausible? As some evidence for this I looked at the time access on the volumes;-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  104857600 Jan 18 13:12 file1.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  104857600 Jan 18 13:12 file2.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  104857600 Jan 18 09:28 file3.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  104857600 Jan 18 09:27 file4.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  104857600 Aug  6 11:36 file5.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  383995904 Jan 18 13:12 filebtree.db-rw-rw-rw-   1 dbadmin  pharaoh  325462016 Jan 18 13:12 filehash.dbas can be seen file1.db (vol1) was accessed at the same time as file2.db (vol2) and both these times are when I ran the application to do the transfer, one record went in and then the -99 error occurred. As a secondary issue I notice that vol5 has not been touched since it was added, does this mean that the scattering algorithm does not add the ALTER TABLE volumes to it\'s list?Hope this helps,Regards,Wm.So what I will do if Unify do not get back by Monday morning, is to recreate RLT\'s database as a single data volume - vol1 - which is NOT preallocated. The root volume vol0 will still be created, as will the btree, and hash volumes. i.e. the data volume will become like the hash and btree volumes. The data volume will be called voldata and the file will be filedata.db. The root volume will be volroot and the file will be file.db. The data base should hopefully be loaded by Monday afternoon.WW - Mon. 21/01/2002 - Have not heard anything from Unify, so I am rebuilding the database as above. Started Load at 11:10am. Looking at last time it will take about 5hrs to load all the data, so provisional finish is 4:10pm. This did not make any difference. I think the problem might be that if there are no records an error -99 is thrown up, as the week_planned test is inside the main cw_job executing loop which only picks all status \'8\' jobs. The week_planned loop might not properly encompass the rest of the code I will have to check tommorrow.WW - Tue. 22/01/2002 - My hunch yesterday was wrong, if there are no matches then all the code is skipped. Barts does not have any jobs with status 8 which planned for week 30.2001, the earliest one they have is week 43.2001. I will wait and see on Friday what happens when they next do there transfer, if they have a hiccup, then I will change the week_planned 43.2001 (cw_job_id = 409093) to a status 8 and see what happens. I am still going to look into it though.WW - Fri. 25/01/2002 - Sent unify support the output of ACLDBDBG for this transfer, there was an error again (-99). The transfer week was 04.2002 (the above transfer week should have been 03.2002 and not 30.2001). I also sent unify the code section which does the insert into ph_hist from the tr_to_hist form. I sent them all the status \'8\' cw_job records left after the transfer, the record which causes the problem has cw_job_id = 421031. The transfer transferred 1319 records, the error ocurred at number 570. The problem record seems to have a week_planned of 52.2001.I have found the problem. The problem is with Docket 407892, which has some hours worked against it, and has a date when responed and a date when completed against it. The problem is that the dates in the hours worked, date responded, and date completed are for the yesr 5201! This makes the elapsed time (tot_hours_resp) - time to respond - to 28050611.98 hrs which does not fit into an amount(6) field. If the date on the hours worked record, and the date responded and the date completed are changed in feedback correction everything should be OK. Speak to Phil Turner on Monday.WW - Mon. 28/01/2002 - spoke to Phil Turner, and explained the problem, and solution. Task closed.', 'Done weekly manual backup then gets database error -99 on transfer to history', 'Mike Bloomfield', 0);
