INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2884, 'Royal Devon & Exeter Healthcare NHS Trust', '2002-02-19 00:00:00', '2002-06-27 00:00:00', '[pj_dets.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.[prj_choice.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.The reason that He wishes to do the above is that he is given the project code by another department, and they reuse their project codes. The new project will have a different account code from the previous project. I will look at archiving and other remedies, including changing the project details report to use the charge code when selecting from ol_dets.I think the easiest thing to do would be to change pj_dets and prj_choice so that when they checked ol_dets for orderlines they do not just use the project_code but use the project_code, cost_centre and account code:...            where  project_code = pj_dets:$project_code            and    line_status <> \'X\'            order by order_number DESC            executing...would become;...            where  project_code = pj_dets:$project_code            and     cost_centre    = pj_dets:$req_by_cost_cent            and    account_code   = pj_dets:$account_code            and    line_status <> \'X\'            order by order_number DESC            executing...FOR prj_choice use:            and     cost_centre    = prj_choice:$req_by_cost_cent_ls            and    account_code   = prj_choice:$account_code_lsWW - Tue. 26/03/2002 - Did the above, but using \'like\' command instaed of \'=\' sign. This allows PWD to still use the current method by using a \'*\' instead of the charge code.WW - Thu. 23/05/2002 - Re-opened. The prj_choice form uses pj_dets:... instead of prj_choice:... as mentioned above. The switch should also not bejust checking if your PWO or not. Create a new pharaoh file variable.WW - Fri. 24/05/2002 - Ammended the code. The pharaoh file variable which switches the feature on if equal to \"Y\" is USE_PRJ_CHARGEI have done SCO. Need to port to AIX and LINUX (and then copy the ports back). Make the SCO patch, update the users with the new com_co.fa file.WW - Tue. 28/05/2002 - Done the patch creation. They just need the patch now.WW - Wed. 28/05/2002 - Downloaded the patch into the downloads directory. Waiting to hear from Neil about when to install it.WW - Wed. 26/06/2002 - Neil Phoned will do the patch and add the variable to the Pharaoh file tomorrow, at around 2.WW - Thu. 27/06/2002 - Done.', 'Trevor Mann wants to be able to reuse a project code for a DIFFERENT project when the original project is dead, i.e. he doesn\'t want the original projects details to appear when he runs the project report.', 'William Wragg', 0);
