INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2892, 'Tower Hamlets Healthcare Trust', '2002-03-08 00:00:00', '2002-03-26 00:00:00', 'KH 080302 - Steve will check backup for corruption and try again, will let us know if happens again.KH 110302 - Same error happening again transferring 46.2001 to history. Dialling on:Operation (+ or -)code section: after field (continue_ss)Operand 1 type undefinedOperand 1 value undefinedoperand 2 type amountoperand 2 value 2.55KH 150302 - emailed Steve requesting a copy of their data (as per WW intruction\'s I assume relate to this).KH 180302 - tape receivedKH 190302 - Loaded tape into data.tower.WW - Mon. 25/03/2002 - An activity code that does not have to be attached to a job can be changed to one that does have to be attached to a job - loosing its charge code in the process - while there are still hours worked records using it. This is what Steve has done. The hrs_wrkd records using the changed activity codes, which were in the system before he changed the activity codes, are not attached to a job, so cannot find a charge code, hence the error. The solution, until we fix the bug, is to SQL the charge code back into the changed activity codes. This will allow the problem hrs_wrkd records which are not attached to a job, to find a charge code from the activity code.KH 260302 - inserted relevant cost centre and account codes into effected activity codes and ran transfer to history for 46.2001 on our copy of the databse. Worked fine. Dialled on and did same on their live database. Call closed.', 'Transferring to P.H. error -2 fx_dets status = -118', 'Mike Bloomfield', 0);
