INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2912, 'Tayside University Hospitals NHS Trust', '2002-04-24 00:00:00', '2002-05-02 00:00:00', 'logged by Gordon.KH 290402 - Cancelling all jobs in current work file for site codes KXH, NWH and DDH for week planned in 2001. Cancel Cuurent Jobs facility not doing all of them. Dialled in. reason not is because bulk of them are status 6 which wont be cancelled. At status as set to that for 3.6 upgrade, not fedback, though some might be now. Godron needs them all out of the system so preparedt o lose any related feedback data. Ran sql to change jobs from staus 6 to status 4.Total number of jobs with site code KXH, NWH and DDH with week planned in 2001 are 9957.Update cw_jobset status_flag = \'4\'where site_code in (\'KXH\',\'NWH\',\'DDH\')and week_planned shlike \'??.2001\'and status_flag = \'6\';9953.Different of four but this is due to jobs with other statuses that should cancel ok. Gordon will come back well has cancel them all, then I will run sql\'s to identify related (fedback) records and delete them for purpose of space.KH 010502 - Gordon has delete all accept one for site KXH which will not delete, error inserting into job_audt status -4.KH 020502 - dialled on, removed duplicate reocrd in job_audt (after outputting to file kate.020502) then cancelled docket 639471. Delete from cw_dets 2434 records that did not exist in cw_job or ph_hist. Delete 1 record from hrs_wrkd (docket 602046) that did not exist in cw_job or ph_hist. Call closed.', 'Job in current work showing as status 6 after being cancelled using \"cancel current jobs\" facility', 'Kate Hamilton', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2913, 'Tower Hamlets Healthcare Trust', '2002-04-24 00:00:00', '2002-05-02 00:00:00', 'Steve has just upgraded from 8.0 to 8.5, and is getting error messages when he tries to refresh his reports.WW - Thu. 25/04/2002 - It appears that any reports with dates will no longer work. The only way to get them to work is to manually edit the sql query. Sent Steve an email telling him this, and the fix that KAte sent unfortunately won\'t work for him.WW - Fri. 26/04/2002 - I have sent an email to Crystal after speaking to them about it, waiting to hear back;--- Crystal email ---Hi,Here are the detail requested:One of our clients has just upgraded their Crystal Reports from 8.0to 8.5. They use Unify Dataserver 6.3AB on SCO OpenServer 5.0.5 withthe Client ODBC Driver \'Unify DBintegrator 5.00.00.06\'The problems they are getting are when they select dates and dateranges, they get a syntax error (ODBC error: [Unify DBIntegrator][DBIntegrator ODBC Driver][DBIntegrator Client][UnifyLNA][UNIFY][Unify DataServer ODBC Driver][Unify DataServer]Syntax error in SQLdynamic statement. (1060)) and then an error in thedatabase.dll The same reports that they are using in 8.5 work finein 8.0. We have replicated the problem on Win98 and win2000 using CrystalReports 8.5 and confirmed that the reports work fine with Version 8.0. The SQL code produced in 8.5 is different from that produced in 8.0;SQL Query from 8.0:SELECT    grn_dets.\"grn_number\", grn_dets.\"account_code\", grn_dets.\"received_val_fld\", grn_dets.\"grn_date\", grn_dets.\"supplier\", grn_dets.\"invoiced_val_fld\",    ol_dets.\"order_number\", ol_dets.\"line_status\"FROM    \"PUBLIC\".\"grn_dets\" grn_dets,    \"PUBLIC\".\"ol_dets\" ol_detsWHERE    grn_dets.\"order_line_no\" = ol_dets.\"order_line_no\" AND    grn_dets.\"order_number\" = ol_dets.\"order_number\" AND    grn_dets.\"financial_year\" = ol_dets.\"financial_year\" AND    grn_dets.\"account_code\" = ol_dets.\"account_code\" AND    grn_dets.\"cost_centre\" = ol_dets.\"cost_centre\" AND    grn_dets.\"financial_period\" = ol_dets.\"financial_period\" AND    grn_dets.\"grn_date\" >= ? AND    grn_dets.\"grn_date\" <= ? AND    ol_dets.\"line_status\" = \'Y\'ORDER BY    grn_dets.\"account_code\" ASCSQL Query from 8.5:SELECT    grn_dets.\"grn_number\", grn_dets.\"account_code\", grn_dets.\"received_val_fld\", grn_dets.\"grn_date\", grn_dets.\"supplier\", grn_dets.\"invoiced_val_fld\",    ol_dets.\"order_number\", ol_dets.\"line_status\"FROM    \"PUBLIC\".\"grn_dets\" grn_dets,    \"PUBLIC\".\"ol_dets\" ol_detsWHERE    grn_dets.\"order_line_no\" = ol_dets.\"order_line_no\" AND    grn_dets.\"order_number\" = ol_dets.\"order_number\" AND    grn_dets.\"financial_year\" = ol_dets.\"financial_year\" AND    grn_dets.\"account_code\" = ol_dets.\"account_code\" AND    grn_dets.\"cost_centre\" = ol_dets.\"cost_centre\" AND    grn_dets.\"financial_period\" = ol_dets.\"financial_period\" AND    grn_dets.\"grn_date\" >= {d \'2000-04-01\'} AND    grn_dets.\"grn_date\" <= {d \'2001-03-31\'} AND    ol_dets.\"line_status\" = \'Y\'ORDER BY    grn_dets.\"account_code\" ASCThe selection wizards look different in 8.0 and 8.5 as well - seeattached jpeg for the 8.0 selection wizard.I hope the above helps, if their is any further information whichI can give you, don\'t hesitate to ask.Regards,Wm.(William Wragg - Pharaoh Development)WW - Thu. 02/05/2002 - Crystal support got back to us with the following advice:You might want to obtain the p2sodbc.dll from Version 8.0 and place it inthe winnt\\system32 directory. Rename the p2sodbc.dll from Version 8.5 first,please.We tried this with Kate\'s Crystsal and my 8.0 p2sodbc.dll (Kate\'s p2sodbc.dll was in her System and NOT System32 folder), and it worked fine. I will send Steve the p2sodbc.dll and the information about what to do with it. Sent Steve the p2sodbc.dll and info.', 'Crystal Reports 8.5 problems.', 'William Wragg', 0);
