INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2982, 'Barts and London NHS Trust', '2002-09-09 00:00:00', '2002-09-12 00:00:00', 'It appears that the PM date last completed record and the Assetdate last completed fields are not updating correctly. If you have alook at the screen dumps I have attached you will see that PM job No.5363 on docket No. 448156 was completed on 26/08/2002, see clock carddetails. Neither the PM or Asset records are showing this as the datelast completed, why?, this is not isolated to this one job it isoccuring across the board.I sent a reply email asking if this was a new problem or not, waiting to hear back.WW - Tue. 10/09/2002 - Got Phils email reply:I have noticed for sometime that the date last done on the assetrecord has been incorrect but for the purposes of reporting on PPM I haveused the date last done from the PPM record. Last Tuesday I was discussingthe PPM loading for one of our sites with the site engineer using a reportwith the date last done taken from the PPM record. The object of the meetingwas to identify Redundant PPM, this we were doing by checking the date lastdone. However during the meeting the engineering supervisor spotted severalPM Jobs that were done every week on a daily basis but the date last donedid not reflect this. Thats when I checked Pharaoh to see if the dates werecorrect, the rest you know as a result of my e-mail.Will look into it when I get the chance.WW - Thu. 12/09/2002 - Did some checking and sent Phil the following findings, via email:The date last done on the PPM record, indicates the date completed of the last docket which was fed back and _not_ the date completed of the most recently transferred PM. So if the docket for the week planned of 34.2002 was fed back _before_ the docket for the week planned of 32.2002, then the date in the date last done field of the PPM record will contain the date from the docket planned for week 32.2002. From your permanent history records I see that the order which the dockets for PM 5363 were fed back is:32.2002 <-- last docket fed back34.200235.200233.200231.2002So PM 5363 has the date last done from the week planned 32.2002 docket.The same applies to the assets. But Assets will not automatically record the date last done. They have to have their \'statutory item\' flag set to \'Y\' (yes) and the PPM record using the asset also needs it\'s \'statutory job\' flag set to \'Y\' (yes). The asset from your example had it\'s flag set to \'N\' and the PPM record had it\'s \'statutory job\' flag set to \'N\'I will wait a day or so to see what he has to say. Phill thanked me and said he would sort out his users so that they complete jobs in the correct order.', 'Phil Lewis sent an email to say that it appears that the PM date last completed record and the Assetdate last completed fields are not updating correctly', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2983, 'Mid-Kent Healthcare NHS Trust', '2002-09-11 00:00:00', '2002-09-19 00:00:00', '[iss_and_pr.fs] : got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended.It appears that the iss_and_pr form only allows reprints if the order header has a status of \'I\' (order_status = \'I\'). I will look into making this \'I\' or \'C\' i.e. look at reprocussions of reprinting closed orders. Perhaps have a switches on the form to say which statuses to include in the reprint. Keith said it would probably be alright. Spoke to Linda she said she would get Hillary to phone me on Monday to arrange for the com_fc_rp.fa to be downloaded and installed with the changed iss_and_pr form.WW - Wed. 18/09/2002 - Installed the update. Kate installed the two patches.', 'Linda and a colleague have created and printed negative variation orders. Linda\'s printed but got mangled in the printer, but her collegues didn\'t even get printed. Both negative VO\'s are now closed but they want to reprint them, but can\'t.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (2984, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2002-09-12 00:00:00', '2003-03-03 00:00:00', 'Installing Tue. 18/09/2002 Done.(1) Remember to set the port back to 8080 rather than just 80.(2) Also if Margery cannot connect to the form, try rebooting the server after the install.(3) Also remember to add the \'nohup\' command in the menu_tomcat file, to the begining of the startup command. This is so that tomcat will carry on running even after the person who has started it logs out.WW - Wed. 18/09/2002 Installed OK. Turned off the email support as I had no details to update the web.xml with. Sent Margery an email outlining how to test it. Will phone her on Friday if she has not phoned me before then. Need to speak to her about backups with the new pharaoh|WEB installed.WW - Mon. 23/09/2002 - put a tomcat shutdown in the backup_before script and a tomcat startup in the backup_extra script. This will allow Aintree to still use the cpio backup.WW - Wed. 25/09/2002 - Received Aintree\'s 5 ODBC license key. Will either speak to Margery when she gets back and phones me, or tomorrow if she doesn\'t phone me today. Need to arrange about a ten minute slot when I can do the ODBC license (licodbc). I also need to know if she has got an email address and SMTP server for me to use. Also is the pharaoh|WEB what she wanted, and if so I will install the final version for her (Need confirmation in writting)WW - Thu. 3/10/2002 - To do:(1) Install ODBC licenses.(2) Install Precompiled version 1g - can download/ftp via modem only 248k uncompressed.(3) Ring David Gordon, for SMTP server, and email address and then add to web.xml. David Rang back, he will speak to Margery about the email address and then get back to me - via email - to give me the email address and a SMTP server ip address.WW - Thu. 10/10/2002 - Will upload the pharaoh|WEB ver. 1h to aintree. I will also license the ODBC for 5 users. The clock will have to be turned back to do this though, so everyone will need to be off. Diane is going to get evryone off for 12 and also arrange for the dialin connection to be enabled.WW - Fri. 11/10/2002 - Done the above, and everything is working. Still waiting to hear about the SMTP server and email address.WW - Thu. 17/10/2002 - Aintree having 2 problems with the pharaoh|WEB ver.1h:(1) Margery getting the following error:java.sql.SQLException: SQLException: Could not execute the query (2) - java.sql.SQLException: [DBIntegrator JDBC Client][UnifyLNA][Unify][Unify DataServer ODBC Driver][Unify DataServer]Attempt to store duplicate value in unique column. (-155) (1254)Will need to dial on and see. Looks like the current_cw_job_id in the control table is out of sync for some reason.Sorted this out, but there was another underlying problem. Sorted that out as well. New release version 1i. I will install this first thing on Monday.(2) One of the people using it are getting the following error:Apache Tomcat / 4.0.4 - HTTPStatus 404 - / faultform.jsptype            Status reportmessage     / faultform.jspdescription: The requested resource (/faultform.jsp) is not availableThis is because faultform.jsp was renamed reqform.jsp in version1h. The user should be going in with:http://<ip address>:8080/jobreqanyway. Told Margery this, and havn\'t heard back about it.WW - Mon. 21/10/2002 - Installed release 1i seems to be working OK. Did notice a slight bug - will fix at some point - if a user enters their data and then submits it, they get the newreq screen, if at this point they click the new request arrow and go to a new screen to enter their new data, but then use the browsers back arrow to go back to the first set of data they entered, they can submit this old data with no problem? Can\'t quite figure out how though.WW - Wed. 11/12/2002 - Finally got the email address and smtp server address, I will phone Margery and ask when she wants me to come on and make the