INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3014, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2002-11-13 00:00:00', '2003-03-12 00:00:00', 'The examples she gave me were 24244(live) and 13334(property). These have four things against them. When Diane tries to split one of the assets in two, ie. by halving the purchase price of the original asset, and then createing a new asset with this halved purchase price, the original asset gains depreciation, when it had non to start with. This is what she says, but she did confess to not seeing the depreciation change when she saved the changed asset, she only noticed it later.If in the ca_dets screen an asset is found and has a \'status\' of \'CI\', an \'IRC\' value > 0 and the the user then modifies the asset in any way, and moves the cursor past the \'Purch Price\' field, then the \'Dep to Date\' will be calculated.The acceptance date must be before the current period and the actual date must be after the current period, otherwise the value will remain at whatever it\'s current value is.I don\'t know if this is what is supposed to happen, but Margery doesn\'t like it. It does seem to be a bug to me. As a temporary solution:When a user makes a change they should store it (F9) WITHOUT first pressing <return>. Then if they have more changes to make they can move to the next field to make their next change where they will save WITHOUT pressing <return>, and so on. If the depreciation gets changed, the user should come out of the record without saving. The depreciation can be removed by using the ammend asset feature, and revalue the asset. This should be done with caution. I do not think that letting the depreciation stay will be a problem but I am not sure. Will speak to Diane tommorrow, and Kate when she gets back.WW - Thu. 14/11/2002 - Spoke to Margery and outlined above. Need to double check all this with Kate, and also see if it actually affects the Depreciation value when doing a charges run, i.e is this extra depreciation added on to the charges run depreciation or is it just ignored and the charges run depreciation go ahead as normal?KH 260203 - patch installed.KH 120303 - no negative feedback re patch. task closed.', 'BUG4 - CC - Diane is trying to split a capital asset into two. The problem is that there is no depreciation on the initial asset, but when they change the purchase price and save the record depreciation appears?', 'William Wragg', 1);
