INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3018, 'Perth Royal Infirmary', '2002-11-18 00:00:00', '2003-02-10 00:00:00', 'Linux and 3.7 installed. Patches done.Scot has placed new box on network on 212.148.124.224Left to do:create users from old machine. (X)copy their custom and upgrade it to LINUX. (X)copy their reports and upgrade them to 3.7 (X)dump their data and reload it on new machine.upgrade reloaded database to LINUX and 3.7WW - Mon. 18/11/2002 - Will dial on and do the users, custom directory and reports. Will phone Scot tomorrow about when to do the dump and reload.WW - Tue. 19/11/2002 - Done. Will speak to Scot about when to dump the database and reload. Will do a test dump and load over the weekend. The users can then try out the new box, and when everything is OK, we can do the real dump and reload. We can get a better idea of how long it will take as well.WW - Fri 22/11/2002 - Dumped.WW - Mon. 25/11/2002 - Loaded. Will try to speak to Scott to say that people can test the database. Spoken to Scott he will get some users to have a go.WW - Tue. 14/01/2003 - Spoke to James, one of the guys there cannot select buttons in the Pharaoh JSB. I said check TERM type should be phawy60. Check they haven\'t altered the mouse mapping. If all these are OK then reinstall the pharaoh JSB from the pharaoh 3.7 install disk.WW - Wed. 22/01/2003 - scheduled the real dump from AIX on Fri. Jan31st after 12pm.The load onto the Linux box will be on Mon. Feb3rd. It should all be done by 1pm.WW - Fri. 31/01/2003 - After some problems getting in (needed to make sure the connection was using the networks default gateway), kicked off the dump.WW - Mon. 03/02/2003 - Dump OK. Some one seems to have re-enabled the backup for Friday. No matter though as the dump was finished before the backup started. Created a new schema.370.small database, and loaded up the dumped data. Ran the upgrade.370 script. Ran disc. Setup the ODBC