INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3068, 'Perth Royal Infirmary', '2003-03-11 00:00:00', '2003-11-17 00:00:00', 'Answer for the first question: They could use the budb backup.Answer for the second question: They can select on management unit and cost centre already. If this isn\'t enough to distinguish the hospitals then we can other criteria. The workshop would not work, as the workshop is not entered into the order. The asset detail would not work either as not all purchase orders are attached to an asset.The best way to go is use the management unit or cost centre (or both).I will speak to Tom Foley tomorrow.WW - Fri. 14/03/2003 - I have been trying all week to get hold of him. I will let Brian sort it.WW - Tue. 22/04/2003 - Spoke to Brian he said speak to Glennis in (Dundee Liff). Spoke to Glennis She seems quite happy with using the Budb, but the other sites have to agree with it. She will tell Tom about it, and he will raise it at the user group meeting. Glennis didn\'t think that just using the management and cost centre would be good enough. She wants to be able to desern - easily - between the hospitals. I will have a think about this.ON HOLD.', 'Tom Foley (Dundee Liff) sent an email asking if people could be logged out of the system for the backup. Also could there be additional criteria for selecting purchase orders to print?', 'William Wragg', 0);
