INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3077, 'Aintree Hospitals NHS TRUST', '2003-03-24 00:00:00', '2003-04-04 00:00:00', 'Looking in the code of index_upd, for the error message, we see that the code checks to see if any records in the pi_index table have a last_updated date which falls within the start and end date of the period trying to be indexed.This can give false results when the user has indexed a previous period in a later period, i.e. they are indexing (and closing periods) a long time after the period should have been closed. The following SQL was used to check the 200203 period (start date 01/10/2002-end date 31/12/2002);select * from pi_indexwhere last_updated is not nulland last_updated >= 01/10/2002and last_updated <= 31/12/2002;The following SQL was used to fix the problem, by changing the last_updated date to before the start date of the 200203 period;update pi_index set last_updated = 28/09/2002where last_updated is not nulland last_updated >= 01/10/2002and last_updated <= 31/12/2002;Ammended the training database for Margery to test with.KH 040403  - Margery said indexation ran fine. Call closed.', 'Margery is trying to run indexation fro the 200203 period. She is getting the error message: ERROR : Indexation has already been run for this period.', 'William Wragg', 0);
