INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3302, 'North Derby CHCS', '2004-09-13 00:00:00', NULL, 'Went in had a look around couldn\'t see anything wrong. Used SQL to set the status flag to 4. Asked Bob Errat to keep an eye on that docket, and to report any problems when printing dockets, as this should never have happened. Closed. (13/09/2004)WW - Thu. 16/09/2004 - Re-opened. Bob has another docket 655221 with the same problem. I have set it to 4. I have trawled through the code to see if I can see what might be happening. The only thing that I can find is that in the fault_report if the week_planned or target_date are changed then the status_flag is set to 2. The problem with this is that a user is not allowed in those fields once the status_flag is greater than 2! I will ask Bob to keep a sharp eye out for peple changing those fields once they\'ve printed the docket. Waiting to see if it happens again.WW - Tue. 28/09/2004 - It\'s happened again. Docket number 656126. The operator said they entered and printed it in the helpdesk, and there were no problems when entering it. I will dial on tomorrow and set to status 4, and do some further investigations next week.WW - Wed. 25/10/2004 - Damned if I can find anything wrong with the code. The status wil, be \'3\' or \'4\' if it is printed. I can\'t see any other way that it can be. The status cannot be changed after its been printed, and none of the code can change the status back to a \'2\'. I cannot reproduce the affect. Asked Bob if the docket has a status \'4\' when it is printed, but he said the printed dockets don\'t have the status on them. If it happens again then I\'ll change the docket report to put the status on the docket temporarily.WW - Fri04mar2005 - It\'s happened again, Bob said it might be something to do with setting the reason for delay to 1 (awaiting spares). I\'ll look into this, in the mean time I\'ll set the job to a status of 4.WW - Tue12jul2005 - It\'s happened again. I went on and had a look, but couldn\'t find it. It turns out that the user just reprinted it, so all though the cw_job_id was the same as the one I was given to check, the docket number had changed, as it had been given a new one. No further action was required. Really need to find out what is causing this.', 'Docket 655158 says it is status 2, but has a docket numbet and the docket issued Y/N flag set to yes. So it should be status 4.', 'William Wragg', 0);
INSERT INTO Tasks (TaskID, CompanyName, date_started, date_finished, details, header, Staff, Bug) VALUES (3303, 'Tower Hamlets Healthcare Trust', '2004-07-27 00:00:00', NULL, 'Develop a pilot consisting of one location and a small group of assets.WW - Tue. 14/09/2004 - Sent rough draft 1b of pilot proposal to Jim O\'Brien. No response.WW - Thu. 23/09/2004 - Sent updated rough draft 1c to Jim O\'Brien.WW - Fri. 24/09/2004 - Starting the development (+ Kates risk_code field ammendment to some tables):[ids_defaults.h]: got, amended,  tested, compiled, put, .changes ammended[as_dets.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[aocontrol.fs/fq]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[rfid_dets.fs/fq]: created, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[com.as]: got, amended, compiled, tested, put, .changes ammended[$PHABASE/lib/schema.381]: created, tested, <databases ammended only data.will>[$PHABASE/upgrade.381/*]: created, tested[rfid webapp]: developing, created, tested, precompiled[rfid deamon]: developing, created, testedWW - Fri. 01/10/2004 - Sent the RFID Pilot stuff to them today. Spoke to to Jim and he said he would speak to Steve and get back to me about what is happening, on Tuesday.WW - Thu. 07/10/2004 - Steve has received the cdrom. Wants to install next week sometime. He has spoken to Tim about the RFID tags.', 'DEVELOPMENT - 3.81 - AO - RFID pilot', 'William Wragg', 0);
